title: easy meatballs and mushroom gravy
directions: Mix ground beef and stuffing and make into meatballs (any size).
Bake or fry meatballs until done.

title: "out of this world" salad
directions: Stir sour cream until smooth.
Add marshmallows and coconut. Add drained fruits and mix.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water (about 235° on candy thermometer). Remove from heat; add margarine and peanut butter. Beat until creamy.
Pour in 11 x 7 dish. Cool and cut in squares.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Pour both cans stewed tomatoes in a bowl and chop until they are in small pieces.
Place half of the tomatoes in a large bowl with ground beef, rice and cottage cheese.
Mix and set aside. Add tomato sauce and tomato paste to remaining stewed tomatoes; stir until smooth.
Core cabbage and steam in a large pot.
Pull leaves off as they become soft.
Lay leaves flat and spoon some meat mixture onto end of each one.
Roll once; fold in sides, then roll.
Spread a little tomato mixture in the bottom of a large pot.
Layer cabbage rolls on top of sauce, adding some tomato mixture over each layer.
Simmer over medium heat for 2 to 3 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix eggs and water in a bowl.
Beat with a wire whip.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly with beater.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake until set, about 45 minutes.

title: fudge sauce
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Blend in water, stirring until cocoa powder is dissolved.
Add evaporated milk and bring to boiling.
Boil gently for 3 to 4 minutes, until sauce thickens, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in margarine and vanilla.
Makes 1 cup of sauce.
Serve warm or cold over ice cream.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Cook on low heat.
After it begins to slow boil, allow it to boil 10 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla. Beat with electric mixer until mixture becomes stiff. Pour into lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: kraut casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.	Add to potato, consomme, kraut, celery seed and brown
sugar.
Place
all in greased casserole and bake 40 minutes at
Especially
good
with
fowl or fish.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Butter casserole baking pan.
Put in vegetables. Pour 1 cup uncooked Minute rice and sprinkle onion flakes on top.

title: marie calendars' cornbread
directions: Mix together with spoon and pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peppered pork roast
directions: Coat roast with seasoning mixture of garlic pepper and rosemary.
Place roast in a shallow pan in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and let roast rest for 5 to 10 minutes before slicing to serve.

title: garden bean salad
directions: Drain all cans of beans; place in a large bowl.
Add green pepper, celery, pimiento and green onions; set aside.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil in a heavy saucepan; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and immediately pour over vegetables. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine the first five ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Mix the last three ingredients and spread over cranberry mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: chili chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken, onion, green pepper and garlic in oil in Dutch oven until chicken loses its pink color.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for about 20 minutes.
You can top this with shredded cheese, green onions or dairy sour cream.

title: croutons
directions: Thinly slice buns; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Brush with Italian dressing.
Bake at 200° overnight.
Can be frozen.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter together.
Mix as much of the powdered sugar as you can into the mixture, then roll into balls (1 inch).
Melt wax and chocolate chips in a double boiler pan. Stir well, then dip balls with toothpicks.
Place on wax paper to cool.
(Can be frozen.) Great for Easter candy eggs or Christmas candy!!!

title: english pea casserole
directions: Pour English peas into casserole dish.
Then spoon mushroom soup over the peas.
Sprinkle crackers over soup and top with cheese.
Cover and cook 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Uncover to brown cheese.

title: jalapeno chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken completely.
Remove from broth, cool and debone. Cook your yellow rice in remaining chicken broth.
If necessary, you may have to add a little more water.
After rice has cooked completely, add chicken, cream of chicken soup, pimientos and jalapeno peppers.
Stir well.
Pour into baking dish and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate overnight. Garnish with paprika for serving.

title: cookie cake
directions: Combine egg and milk.
Add cake mix and chopped pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chocolate chips and Heath bits. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: date balls
directions: Combine sugar, butter, dates, egg and salt in a saucepan. Cook 10 minutes on medium heat, stirring to prevent burning. Cool.
Add Rice Krispies, pecans and vanilla.
Stir well.
Make balls and roll in confectioners sugar or coconut.

title: lemon-lime salad
directions: Mix lemon jello, lime jello and boiling water.
Add cold water.
Let this begin to gel.
Mix pineapple and evaporated milk. Add to jello mixture and let it gel more.
Mix mayonnaise, cottage cheese, nuts, salt and mustard.
Mix in and gel until hard.

title: hines ham roll-up
directions: Pat ham slices dry with a paper towel.
Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Chop green olives and mix with the softened cream cheese.
Spread mixture on ham slice (fairly thin).
Roll up and chill.
After 2 hours, slice in pinwheels.
Kids and adults love them!

title: twin meat loaves
directions: Soak bread in the milk, add eggs and beat with rotary beater. Add meat, onion, celery, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper; mix thoroughly.
Form into 2 loaves.
Place into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex or glass cake pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Glaze with catsup and corn syrup and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: orange yogurt shake
directions: Place juice, yogurt and banana in blender container.
Cover; process until well blended.
Add ice cubes; process until cubes are crushed.
Makes two 1-cup servings.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve liquid.
Halve slices.
Melt butter in a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan.
Stir in brown sugar and 1 tablespoon reserved pineapple liquid.
Add water to remaining liquid to make 2/3 cup.
Arrange pineapple and cherries in pan. Combine flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Beat shortening about 30 seconds.
Add granulated sugar; beat until well combined.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute.
Add dry ingredients and the 2/3 cup liquid alternately to beaten mixture, beating after each addition.
Spread in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; invert onto a plate.
Serve warm. Serves 8.

title: irish cream
directions: Blend 3 to 5 minutes in blender.
Keep in fridge.

title: 24-hour layered vegetable salad
directions: Layer bits of lettuce in 9 x 13-inch dish, making a thick layer.
Top with a layer of thinly sliced scallions.
Add a layer of thinly sliced celery.
Add frozen peas.
Top with crumbled bacon bits.
Mix 1 1/2 cups mayonnaise plus 2 tablespoons sugar and spread on top.
Spread 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese over layered salad.
Seal with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with egg slices.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Place bacon and cheese in prepared pie shell.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Pour over bacon and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool before serving.
Yield:
6 servings

title: pick up sticks
directions: Dip sausage in egg.
Combine saltine crumbs with chili powder. Roll sausages in saltine mixture to coat evenly.
Insert toothpick in on end of each sausage.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until hot.
Serve with catsup as dip. Makes 14 sticks.

title: cheesy brat stew
directions: Cut brats up.
Place in a large skillet with potatoes, green beans, onion, cheese, soup and water.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: simple turned bread
directions: Have hot lard or oil in cast-iron skillet.
Pour or spoon batter in small amounts and turn when brown on bottom.
Brown on top.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together first three ingredients and press into glass pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator.
Mix next three ingredients and pour over nut mixture.
Mix instant pudding with milk according to recipe on box.
Pour over Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: cherry brownies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil, then beat.
Sift flour with cocoa and salt and add to egg, sugar and oil mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Turn into 2 greased pans (8 x 8 x 2-inch) or one long pan (13 x 9-inch) and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and egg with fork and press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar in a small deep bowl and beat 5 minutes.
Pour over first mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: joann's buttermilk biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in buttermilk; knead dough gently. Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter. Bake on lightly greased pan at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yield: 10 biscuits.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain fat.
Add chili powder, garlic, sauce, tomatoes, salt and simmer 20 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with tortillas.
Top with half meat mixture, then half the cheese.
Repeat tortillas, meat mixture and cheese. Bake at 350° about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade dumplings
directions: Have broth boiling easy and carefully spoon in the dumplings. Cover and cook gently for 5 minutes.
Turn off heat and let steam for 5 minutes.

title: bruschetta
directions: Run 1/2 tablespoon red wine vinegar, olives, garlic and olive oil through food processor.
Store up to two days in refrigerator.

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop first 6 ingredients; then add milk.
Pack in a greased loaf pan.
Bake about 30 or 40 minutes or until slightly brown at 350°.
Will keep a long time wrapped and stored in refrigerator.

title: basic spaghetti sauce
directions: In large 8-quart or large pot, cook onion (leave sliced long to remove easily) and garlic in oil.
Remove onion and garlic with slotted spoon.
Drain any liquid back into pan.
Onion should be cooked slowly until they begin to brown; do not burn.
Remove pot from heat.
Put in tomato paste; return to heat and cook slowly, stirring often.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Do not let stick (best to use Teflon pot).
Add tomato sauce, sugar and salt.
Simmer at least 3 hours.
Can add seafood, meat or fowl to this basic sauce. Can freeze.
Makes 7 to 8 quarts.

title: molasses crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg. Mix together flour, soda and salt, then add to butter mixture alternating with molasses and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased pans.
Bake 12 minutes.

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Stir in vanilla and food coloring.
Add corn flakes.
Drop on wax paper in shape of wreath. Add red hots on top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all filling ingredients together and pour into pie shell. Bake ten minutes at 400°, then 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, juice and extracts.
Gradually add sugar.
Add in 3rds, beating well 4 well beaten eggs.
Blend in dry ingredients in 4ths.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 10 minutes in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan (greased and floured).
Have ingredients at room temperature.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Top with crushed cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: apple peelings sauce
directions: Select and wash best looking apple peelings in cold water. Place in medium-size pot along with other ingredients and boil for 1 hour over medium heat.
Then lower heat, cook sauce until thick. Put sauce in jars that are heated in warm water.
Let jars stay in warm water until they seal.
Sauce may be eaten with meats and dressing.
Yields 1/2 dozen 4-ounce jars.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil until creamy (will not get fluffy; will still have sugar crystals); add flour, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Beat.
Add carrots and mix.
(I add about 1 cup of nuts to my batter; but that is optional.)
Bake 30 to 40 minutes; cool and ice.

title: garden vegetable dip
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add the vinegar, oil and garlic salt.
Set overnight and drain.
Use corn chips to dip.

title: cheese ball
directions: Make into ball and cover with paprika.
Refrigerate and let seasoning mix for couple days.

title: nutmeg sauce
directions: Cream butter in saucepan.
Gradually add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg yolk, flour, vanilla and gradually add boiling water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in nutmeg (sprinkle in nutmeg, it will clump).
Makes about two cups.

title: bowman's pot pie
directions: To flour, add a little salt and eggs; rub into flour as you do shortening for a pie crust.
Add sweet milk, enough to make a soft dough.
Roll thin and cut in squares.
Have meat broth with pieces of meat and potato chunks in it boiling, and drop in squares of dough one at a time.
Roll out more dough and continue dropping until all dough is gone.
Be certain that the broth is always boiling when adding more dough.
Cook until the potatoes are done.

title: jack daniel's cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: cavetelli and broccoli
directions: Cook cavetelli in boiling water as directed on package.
While cavetelli is cooking, saute garlic in margarine and olive oil until tender.
Add thawed, drained broccoli.
Drain cavetelli in large bowl.
Toss cavetelli with broccoli mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: chasin chili (for 10 people)
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes. Saute peppers in oil for 5 minutes.
Add onions and cook while stirring.
Add garlic and parsley.
Melt butter and saute meats for 15 minutes.
Add meats to onion mixture.
Stir in chili powder and cook 10 minutes.
Add to beans and add rest of spices and mix. Simmer, covered, for 1 hour and uncovered for 30 minutes.
Skim off fat.
Will feed 10 people.
Delicious!

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil over medium heat. Stir constantly. Remove from heat and add peanut butter. Stir until smooth. Add corn flakes. Stir until coated well. Drop by tablespoon on waxed paper and let cool.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Add cream cheese. Add pineapple and juice, chopped nuts and chopped celery.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan and refrigerate.
This keeps well!

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix well.
Roll out paper-thin on floured surface.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Cut into thin strips.
Let dry an hour or so. You can freeze them.
Cook in bubbling broth until tender.

title: dilled new potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes, cut into quarters, do not peel.
Cook until just tender, do not overcook.
Cool down in strainer with cold water.
Cook peas in boiling water until done.
Drain and flush with cold water.
When peas and potatoes are cool, add onion (sliced thin in partial rings), mayonnaise (1/2 cup at a time), sour cream and dill.
Mix well.
Mixture should be nicely coated with mayonnaise, not swimming.
Salt lightly to taste.

title: cream cheese braid
directions: Heat sour cream over low heat.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter. Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over water in a large mixing bowl until dissolved.
Add sour cream mixture, eggs and flour; mix well. Cover tightly, refrigerate overnight.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare and slice apples.
Sift dry ingredients together (sugar, salt and flour) and mix with apples.
Line pie pan (8 3/4 inch round by 1 3/4 inch deep) with pie crust, fill with apple mixture. Dot with butter.
For top mix dry pie crust mix, slivers of butter and sugar to taste.
Bake in very hot oven at 450 degrees for 15 minutes, reduce temperature to moderate oven 350 degrees and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix hot water, salt, sugar and shortening together.
Dissolve yeast in warm water (about 5 minutes).
Add 2 cups flour to water, sugar, shortening mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg and dissolved yeast.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in remaining flour one cup at a time.
Place dough in greased bowl.
Brush top with soft shortening.
Cover tightly with foil or bowl cover. Store in refrigerator until double in bulk or until needed.
When ready to use, punch down and cut off dough.
Shape rolls, place cut side down, in pan.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 18 to 24 medium rolls.
Dough may be kept a week.

title: chicken in orange sauce
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and set aside.
Flatten chicken some (1/4 inch recommended).
In a skillet, saute chicken in water until lightly browned on both sides.
Pour orange sauce mixture over chicken.
Simmer uncovered 6 to 8 minutes or until chicken is cooked, basting occasionally.
Spoon sauce over chicken and serve with rice pilaf or couscous.
Nice with a garnish of oranges and kiwi fruit.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Make raspberry Jell-O according to directions on package.
Put through a food chopper the cranberries and oranges (quartered and seeds removed).
Add sugar and nuts and celery, if desired.
Mix well.

title: crab and spinach dip
directions: Saute onions in butter; mix in remaining ingredients and serve with chips in a chafing dish.

title: banana pudding
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt; gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of mixture into egg yolks; return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: company corn
directions: Mix all together except for cheese.
Bake in buttered casserole for 1 hour at 350°.
Put cheese on to melt after corn is done.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Debone salmon as much as possible and drain; mash up.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add egg.
Add flour and work enough plain cornmeal into mixture that it can be made into patties to fry (not too wet).
Get oil medium hot and pattie out into oil.
Fry (medium) until brown and turn over and fry until brown.

title: orange cream salad
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar until light and smooth. Gradually blend in milk. Dissolve jello in hot water. Cool slightly. Gradually add milk mixture. Stir in orange rind and juice. Pour into mold. Chill until firm.

title: chicken vegetable stir-fry
directions: In skillet over high heat, in 2 tablespoons hot oil, stir-fry chicken until no longer pink.
Remove; set aside.
In same skillet in 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir-fry vegetables with garlic until tender-crisp.

title: baked succotash
directions: Soak black beans overnight.
Keep changing the water until all the black color is gone.
Mix beans, corn, onion and milk.
Fry bacon and chop up.
Mix grease, bacon and salt; add to bean mixture.
Mix flour and water together and mix in bean mixture. Put in baking dish and bake at 350° until corn is done.

title: hors d'oeuvres for 10
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch dish (do day ahead):

bean dip, guacamole (room temperature), taco seasoning mix, sour cream, green onions, olives, small pieces of tomatoes (chop together and put on top sour cream layer) and shredded cheese is the last layer.
Use tortilla chips to dip.

title: less fat lasagna
directions: Boil noodles 8 to 10 minutes and dry.
Mix together spaghetti sauce, cottage cheese, sugar and Parmesan cheese over low heat. Spray an 8 x 12-inch dish with Pam spray.
Pour 1/2 cup of sauce mix in bottom of dish.
Lay 3 noodles on sauce.
Cover with sauce mix, then Mozzarella cheese.
Continue until 3 layers high.
Top with reserved 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in 350° oven (glass or metal pan) for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings, 7 ounces each.
Each serving contains 269 calories and 8 grams of fat.

title: chocolate biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Combine flour, coconut, sugar, cocoa, and whipping cream in food processor bowl.
Process until mixture forms a dough. Turn out onto a floured surface and knead gently about 6 times.
Roll to a thickness of about 1/2 inch or a little less. Cut with a 2 inch biscuit cutter. Dip into melted butter and be sure the biscuits are coated with butter on both sides.
Place on a baking sheet spacing the biscuits about 2 inches apart.
Bake for about 15 minutes or until no longer doughy.
Place biscuits on a rack with wax paper underneath the rack.

title: aunt meryle's coconut pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except water, sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake for 1 hour in 350°
oven in a greased tube pan. While cake is cooling in pan, make glaze of sugar, water and vanilla.
Bring to a boil.
Punch holes in cake with toothpick and pour glaze slowly over cake while still hot.

title: kernals chicken
directions: Combine pancake mix with 1 package dressing mix.
Combine the other dressing mix with the egg and soda.
Dip each piece of chicken into the egg mixture, then the pancake mixture.
Place on a paper towel for about 5 minutes.
Put cooking oil in pan or electric skillet and heat to 425°.
Brown chicken good, then put on a sheet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: watermelon rind pickle
directions: Cut prepared watermelon rind (green removed, a little pink left on) into squares.
Cover with boiling water. Boil until fork will penetrate; do not overcook.
Drain and place in enamel pan or large bowl.

title: onion pie
directions: Partially bake crust.
Saute onions in oil and butter over low heat until golden yellow.
Beat eggs, half and half, flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Add onions and half of the grated cheese. Pour into crust.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: sauerkraut spareribs
directions: Cover spareribs with applesauce, anise seed and sauerkraut. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Very good.

title: chocolate cake icing
directions: Bring to rapid boil and boil for 1 minute.
Whip and spread.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add to berries and lemon juice. Add butter.
Heat over medium heat until boiling.
Boil for about 5 minutes.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Place pastry on top and sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
I usually double this amount for a 9 x 13-inch pan for cobblers.

title: family goulash
directions: Bring 6 cups water to a boil.
Add 4 ounces noodles to water. Stir often and boil until tender.
Cook and stir ground beef, onion and garlic in a large skillet until beef is brown and onions and garlic are tender.
Drain off fat.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Add 7-Up in 3 parts, pouring slowly. Beat with mixer. Do not overbeat. Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes or until springs back.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Add oil, eggs and milk; beat.
Add corn and beat; mix well. Add meal and flour.
Beat and add peppers and onions (use just a medium-size onion grated, does not matter).
Pour half of mixture in greased pan and sprinkle cheese over it.
Add the rest with cheese on top.
Cook at 375° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar. Add melted butter and vanilla. Beat well. Stir in flour and pecans. Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: santa snowflake cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites; add vanilla and salt. Continue beating until fairly firm; add sugar gradually, beating until very stiff.
Drop from spoon onto a cookie sheet covered with greased aluminum foil.
Put in oven and turn off oven heat immediately.
Leave in oven several hours until oven cools thoroughly.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Combine chicken, water and salt in large boiler.
Bring to boil and simmer until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth reserving 3 cups broth in boiler.
Cut up chicken into bite size pieces and set aside.
Add potatoes and carrots to broth. Bring to boil.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Add chicken, corn, tomato sauce and pepper and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: cedric's casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add ground meat, salt and pepper. Saute cabbage.
In a 2-quart baking dish, place 1/2 cabbage on bottom.
Place ground meat mixture on top of cabbage and cover with remaining cabbage.
Pour a large can of tomato soup on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In a shallow glass bowl, combine the orange juice and cornstarch.
Stir in chicken.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours. Drain chicken.
In a small bowl, combine broth and soy sauce.
Set aside.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and stir until smooth.
Serve with all kinds of fruit.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese until fluffy.
Add flavorings; beat well.
Add eggs one at a time, stir in flour. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° in tube pan.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Cut six tortillas into 1/2 to 1/4 inch strips.
Set aside. Cut remaining tortillas into strips also.
Fry these in hot oil until crisp.
Set aside.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes as directed, except no butter.
Add all other ingredients; mix gently.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Cut 2 large sweet potatoes in slices.
Cook over medium-high heat until soft.
Drain and mash (3 cups).
Mix all ingredients; pour into baking dish.

title: crumb topping
directions: Mix dry ingredients well, then add oleo or butter.
Mix with fork until crumbly; ready to use.
Can be refrigerated for later use.

title: tuna, egg and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Drain tuna.
Hard boil the eggs.
Can add more mustard and mayonnaise.
Mix everything together.
Could be eaten warm but it is better if it sets overnight.
You could add other ingredients like onions, etc.

title: cheese pecan ball
directions: Mix cheeses and onion by hand.
Add salt, pepper, 1/2 cup parsley and 1/2 cup pecans.
Shape into a ball.
Roll the ball in remaining parsley and pecans.
Makes 3 nice sized cheese balls.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Spread cheese across bottom of pan. Spread chili on top of cheese; top with shredded cheese. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. A hit every time!

title: boiled custard
directions: Stir sugar, flour, eggs and salt until well mixed.
Use double boiler.
Add mixture to scalded milk.
Keep water boiling hot. Stir until custard coats spoon.
Strain and add vanilla.
Cool. This is a drinking custard.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Add taco seasoning mix packet. Add refried beans.
Spread in 9-inch square pan.
mix sour cream and green taco salsa.
Spread on top of meat bean mixture.
Top with shredded taco cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: kuchen topping
directions: Cook 1 cup sugar, whipping cream and brown sugar very, very slowly in a heavy aluminum pan for about 1/2 hour.
Add butter. Cool and beat to a pudding consistency.
Spread 1/2 mixture on roll dough after shaping in a 9 1/2 to 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes. Spread remaining cream mixture on warm kuchen.

title: layered mexican dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in pan and drain.
Add taco seasoning and follow directions on package.
Place in bottom of dish.
Layer as follows:
Layer 2, 1 can refried beans; Layer 3, salsa and Layer 4, grated cheese.
Heat all in oven until cheese melts.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream and peppers.
Serve with chips.

title: gram's doughnuts
directions: Beat sugar, shortening, vanilla and eggs together.
Add all the other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight before frying.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Prepare Jell-O as usual, except add the frozen strawberries instead of cold water.
Chill until almost set.
Beat until foamy. Fold in Cool Whip.
Cut cake into bite-size pieces and add to Jell-O mixture.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: lemon yogurt cheese cake
directions: In blender, blend yogurt and Ricotta cheese until smooth. Combine eggs, sugar and flour until smooth and add to blended cheese mixture; blend.
Add vanilla and salt; blend.
Add juice and peel; blend.
Pour into greased 8-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Mix
sugar,
water
and syrup and cook until it threads when poured from a spoon.
Pour mixture over beaten egg whites and beat
until
stiff	and
cool.
Add
powdered sugar until mixture is thick.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat in oven until melted.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over butter; press down with fork.
Layer 1 cup of peanut butter chips over crumbs; sprinkle coconut over chips.
Layer remaining 2/3 cup peanut butter chips over coconut.
Drizzle sweet milk evenly over top.
Bake 20 minutes.
Microwave on High the shortening and chocolate chips for 1 minute.
Stir.
Continue until chips are melted and mixture.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and then beaten egg yolk.
Sprinkle 1 cup flour over the fruit and nuts.
Add spices and salt to remaining flour.
Combine butter, fruit and flour.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: butter cheese squares
directions: Grease
and
flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make a crust of the cake mix, margarine and 1
egg.
Press
in pan.
Combine cream cheese, 2
eggs
and sugar with a mixer.
Mix until smooth and pour
over crust.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar after baking.
Cut into squares.

title: babka (noodle pudding)
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until almost done; drain.
Place in a mixing bowl with butter; toss to coat.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs, milk and sugar until well blended. Combine with noodles.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until puffy and noodles begin to brown at edges.
Cut into squares and serve hot or cold with fruit preserves.
Yields 12 servings.

title: whipping cream biscuits
directions: Put flour in mixing bowl.
Slowly add whipping cream.
Mix until it forms a dough.
Pat out.
Additional flour may be added if dough becomes too sticky.
Cut out biscuits.
This makes 10 to 12 biscuits.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Broil and season chicken breasts.
In a skillet, combine stewed tomatoes, celery, green bell peppers and Cajun spices.
Simmer while chicken is cooking.
When chicken is done, put into tomato sauce and simmer while preparing the rice.
When rice is done, serve chicken and tomatoes over the rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sunny salad
directions: Pour over vegetables and mix to cover. Chill for at least one hour. Before serving, crush 6 strips of crisp bacon and 1/4 cup sunflower seeds- optional- over top.

title: orange fruit dip
directions: Mix together and serve with fruit.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
Also freezes well.
Thaw in fridge.

title: gourmet cheese ball
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: ice cream cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Fill cones 3/4 full with batter.
Place filled cups upright in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° (test with toothpick).
Frost generously when cooled and put sprinkles on.

title: brownies
directions: Bake brownies in round cake pan according to the cake version of package directions.
When cool, cover with cherry pie filling. Pipe edges with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter. Add cocoa, sugar and milk and bring to a boil for 1 minute. Then remove from heat and add vanilla, nuts, oats and peanut butter. Mix well and drop by spoon on wax paper. Yield: 2 dozen.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, Crisco, salt and sugar until crumbly. Beat water, egg and vinegar and add to flour mixture.
Makes 7 to 8 pie crusts.

title: can't stop eating dip
directions: Heat first 2 ingredients.
Serve with Fritos.

title: healthy bars
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with no-stick spray.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and combine.
Add the bran and buttermilk and sift in the flour, soda and salt.
Stir just until well mixed.
Stir in nuts and fruit.
Bake until edges are lightly browned, about 20 minutes.
Test with clean straw to make sure center is done.
Cool completely in the pan on a wire rack.
Cut into bars and wrap each bar in foil, for carrying on hikes.
These travel well if treated with some care (don't put them on the bottom of your pack).
They keep well but should be frozen if made far in advance.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in an 8-inch square baking pan.
Mix together flour, baking powder, sugar and milk.
Pour over butter, but do not mix.
On top of batter, pour prepared fruit pie filling.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: mushroom bacon green beans
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving 3 tablespoons of drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add mushrooms and onion to drippings in skillet. Saute until onion is tender.
Add beans and pepper, cooking until thoroughly heated.
Place in serving dish and top with crumbled bacon.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: In ungreased 8-inch square pan, mix flour, sugar, 1/2 cup cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix milk and oil.
Add into flour mixture.
Mix will look stiff.
Mix brown sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa and chocolate chips.
Sprinkle over batter.
Mix vanilla and hot water.
Pour over all of the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
When done, will look like brownies.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: shrimp wheels
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients, except for dough, which you need to unroll and separate into 4 rectangles.
Spread approximately 1/4 cup shrimp mixture on rectangles.
Starting at short end, roll up like a jelly roll.
Cut the rolls in 10 pieces and place them on a greased baking sheet, flat side down.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot. Makes 40 pieces.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, bread and milk; set aside.
In blender, mix egg, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix this with beef mixture. Roll into 30 balls.
Roll in flour and brown in 2 tablespoons oil. Drain, then add tomato juice, water, celery, carrots and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer; pour over meat balls and simmer 45 minutes.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: eggs and sausage bake
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Mix eggs and milk. Add bread, cheese and sausage. Pour into 8 x 11-inch glass pan (lightly greased) and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand a few minutes to cool. Serves 8 to 10.

title: deviled seafood
directions: Stir together all ingredients until blended.
Spoon into a 1-quart shallow casserole dish or 8 ovenproof shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add soup and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add mushrooms and cooked broccoli.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° or until cheese bubbles.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Cook oleo and sugar for 2 minutes until it forms.
Pour over graham crackers with nuts on top.
Use a cookie sheet with sides. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, then flour and pecans. Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes on cookie sheet in 300° oven.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: tetrazzini
directions: Save some cheese for top.

title: spiced sweet oranges
directions: Up to 3 days ahead:
Squeeze enough juice from lemons to equal 3 tablespoons; cut remaining lemons into 1/4-inch thick slices. Set lemon slices aside.
Tie 1 tablespoon cloves in cheesecloth to make a spice bag.
In 3-quart saucepan over high heat, heat spice bag, lemon juice, sugar, cinnamon sticks, bay leaves, kumquats and 5 cups water to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour spice-syrup mixture into large bowl; discard spice bag.

title: pinto beans a la villa montana
directions: Wash beans.
Place in pressure cooker with water and cook about 35 minutes until soft but not mushy.
Do not salt or season while cooking beans under pressure as this changes flavor.
Saute onions in the bacon fat until almost brown and then add garlic. Pour cooked beans on top of this mixture and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add hot chili pepper and salt. Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese straws
directions: Soften butter and cheese together.
Sift flour, salt and red pepper together.
Combine mixture and work until very smooth. Divide in half and roll on floured surface.
Roll out very thin and cut in long strips, approximately 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: gourmet tuna bake
directions: Cook noodles; drain and rinse.
Put half in layer in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Crumble drained tuna fish evenly over this layer.
Cover with remaining noodles.
Pour soup over this layer.
Top with crumbled potato chips.
Dot with the butter.
Pour sherry over the top.
Do not cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes until bubbly and golden brown.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix contents of vegetable/seasoning packet, water and butter in small boiler.
Heat until margarine is melted; pour into 12x8 inch baking dish.
Stir in stuffing crumbs and 1/2 of salsa. Place chicken over stuffing.
Pour remaining salsa over chicken. Cover with foil.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Stir in milk gradually.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into pie shell.
Cook until serving time.

title: cole slaw
directions: Toss shredded cabbage and mixture of remaining ingredients with Eggless Mayonnaise or Thousand Island Dressing*.

title: no-nonsense nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Dip tortillas in water.
Shake off excess water.
Cut into wedges.
Bake 3 minutes.
Turn.
Bake 2 more minutes. Decrease oven to 400°.
Place beans in colander and rinse with water until water runs clear. Place beans and chili powder in bowl and mash.
Spread into pie pan. Cover with salsa and top with cheese. Bake 20 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan; blend in flour.
Add milk gradually and cook about 3 minutes, stirring until a thick sauce is formed.
Add the salmon, 1 egg and 1 cup bread crumbs.
Mix and add salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour onto a platter and let cool. Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour or longer.
Shape into desired shapes.
Heat to medium-high heat a skillet half full of oil. Beat other egg in bowl.
Spread remaining bread crumbs on platter. Dip each first in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Fry until brown. Drain and serve.

title: cherry cheese cake(no bake)
directions: Mix the crushed crackers, butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar and spread in cake pan.

title: mango salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling liquid of mango juice and water. Set aside.
Put drained mangos and cream cheese into blender and blend until creamy.
Add to jello mixture and stir in lime juice. Pour into ring mold, individual molds or oblong pan.
Chill 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Serve on bed of lettuce and top with any or all of sour cream, brown sugar and coconut.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine; stir in dressing mix.
Use 1/2 of this mixture to line casserole.
Mix all other ingredients and pour into lined casserole.
Sprinkle remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cooked salad
directions: Mix flour and sugar; pour over pineapple.
Top with cheese. Crush crackers and place on top.
Bake at 325° until bubbly (20 minutes).

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Add all other ingredients.
Shape into ball.
Roll in nuts and chill.

title: cheesies
directions: Blend well; roll into 3 rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper; place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice thin.
Bake in a 300° oven.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Combine sugar and oil or applesauce in a medium mixing bowl; beat at medium speed (electric mixer) 2 minutes or until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat until light and lemon colored.

title: best corn in ohio
directions: Stir together and bake until firm in center, approximately one hour at 350°

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Bring water, carrots and butter to a boil in saucepan.
Stir in Stove Top mix; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Place chicken in greased baking dish.
Top with stuffing.
Mix sour cream and cheese; spoon over stuffing.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Mix pudding as directed. Crumble 1/2 of cake into bottom of punch bowl.
Spread 1/2 of pudding over top of cake.
Spread 1/2 of pineapple (drained) over pudding.
Spread 1/2 of cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Spread 1/2 Cool Whip over cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle 1/2 of coconut over Cool Whip. Sprinkle 1/2 pecans over coconut and then start all over again.

title: fish gelatin mold
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese until blended.
Combine 1/4 liquid saved from shrimp with the gelatine.
Combine all ingredients. Put in greased mold.
Refrigerate.
Can be frozen.
Unmold.
Serve with crackers.

title: chipped beef and chicken
directions: Wrap each
chicken
breast
with a slice of bacon, then the chipped
beef.
Secure with a toothpick.
Put in casserole dish. Mix
soup
and
sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 4 hours at 250°.
(Cover
casserole
for first 2 hours of cooking.) This can be made ahead and frozen.
Serves 8.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Put mayonnaise in bowl; cut green onion and dice.
Add to mayonnaise along with parsley and quartered lemon.
Add to mixture. Add pickles and pimento pieces.
Put into blender and cover; blend 1 to 2 minutes.
Should be of a coarse consistency.
Serve with all varieties of fish and seafood.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: cream of leek soup
directions: Saute leeks and onion in 2-quart pot in margarine for 10 minutes.
Add 2 cups broth and shredded potatoes.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Remove 1/2 and puree.
Return to other 1/2 and add cream and chicken stock (more if too thick).
Serve and sprinkle with parsley and bacon bits.

title: fireside supper
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally. Yields 6 servings.

title: lemon custard pudding cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar. Beat egg yolks.
Add to mixture, along with milk.
Add lemon peel; mix well.
Add lemon juice.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff; slowly add remaining 1/2 cup sugar while beating. Fold into batter.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Place in a shallow pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with confectioners sugar dusting. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy sauteed zucchini
directions: Heat oil in large nonstick skillet.
Add zucchini and half of garlic.
Saute until zucchini is softened, about 10 minutes.
Add remaining garlic, salt and pepper flakes to zucchini mixture.
Let cool to room temperature.
To serve, sprinkle the zucchini with vinegar.

title: oriental salad
directions: Dressing:
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper with the seasonings packet.
Let stand several hours.

title: sausage balls with cheese
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook over low heat until brown on all sides.
Drain on paper towels. Combine flour, salt, paprika and cheese.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender.
It will be dry.
Mix with hands until dough is smooth.
Shape dough around the cooked sausage ball.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May be frozen before cooking.
Yields 4 dozen balls.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Scrub
carrots.
Slice	and boil in salted water for 10 minutes.
Add
onion
and	bell
pepper.
Meanwhile,
combine tomato sauce, vinegar, salad oil and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add Tabasco sauce.
Pour over carrots and refrigerate.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix soup, broth and vegetables.
Bring to boil.
Pour over chicken.
Mix melted margarine, flour, buttermilk, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture. Bake about 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars with shortenings.
Add eggs and increase speed of mixer to high.
Beat until mixture turns lighter color brown. Add vanilla.
Add flour/baking soda/salt and mix.
Add chocolate chips.
Spoon onto cookie sheet, leaving plenty of space to spread.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 12 minutes.
Should look slightly shiny and undercooked when you remove from oven to maintain the chewy texture when cooled.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs; stir in apples.
In another bowl stir together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture and stir well.
Stir in nuts, milk and vanilla. Pour batter in greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle with sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool before slicing.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and peppers; cover with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Add red peppers, vinegar, spices and sugar. Cook 40 minutes.
Put into jars and seal tops.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together.
Stir in the seasonings (crush to make finer).
Mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: hungry boys' casserole
directions: Saute beef, celery, onion, green pepper and garlic in large skillet until vegetables are tender; drain.
Add tomato paste, water, monosodium glutamate, salt and paprika.
Reserve 1 cup for biscuits.
Add pork and beans and chickpeas or lima beans.
Simmer while preparing biscuits.

title: joan's brownies
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs.
Melt butter and cocoa.
Add to sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat for 30 seconds. Add milk.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Add crushed vanilla wafers.
Cook in a 2-pound loaf pan or tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: bread starter
directions: Mix yeast, water and sugar with water and flour in a glass jar.
Cover with a cloth and fasten with a rubber band.
Keep at room temperature for 5 days.
It should be foamy and have a yeasty aroma.
Feed and store in refrigerator.

title: allyson cook's party chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice, lemon-pepper seasoning and salt.
Chill several hours.
Add celery, grapes or cherries, chopped eggs, mayonnaise and almonds; toss lightly.
Season salad with salt to taste.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: rice pudding(reduced calorie)
directions: Beat eggs in casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cornish hens with mushroom rice
directions: Seasons hens with salt and pepper, in and out.
In small pan, cook onion and rice in butter 5 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
After cooking, add water, bouillon cube, lemon juice and salt to rice.
Reduce heat.
Cook slowly 20 to 25 minutes until liquid is absorbed and rice is fluffy.
Stir in mushrooms. Stuff birds with rice.
Place breast up in shallow pan.
Brush with margarine.
Place in 400° oven, covered, for 30 minutes. Uncover; roast 1 hour longer.
When done, leg will twist easily. During last 15 minutes, brush with margarine.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Precook broccoli; drain and cool.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing; set aside.
Mix onion soup, cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Fold in cooled broccoli.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing on bottom of casserole pan.
Add broccoli mixture.
Spread remaining 1/2 of stuffing on top.
Cover and bake for 40 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Blend avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper (a blender or a hand mixer works very well); set aside.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix; set aside.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck.
In large pot, combine all ingredients; bring to a boil and simmer.

title: garlic roasted potatoes(preparation: 10 minutes. baking: 25 minutes.  servings: 4.)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place garlic, butter and water in small saucepan; simmer until water evaporates and garlic is tender. Strain butter; mash soft garlic through very fine strainer.
Toss potatoes in garlic butter; place in single layer in large baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes, turning potatoes occasionally, until they are tender and browned.
Remove potatoes from baking dish with slotted spoon.
Season with salt and pepper before serving.

title: hot sausage cheese puffs
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine sausage, cheese, biscuit mix and water in bowl; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls; place 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: raisin cake
directions: Pour water over raisins and let set all night. Be sure the raisins are the sticky kind.
Add soda to raisins.
Pour water off and later add it to mixture.
Add raisins to butter and sugar. Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. then change to 250° for 30 minutes.

title: white castle hamburgers
directions: Mix beef, broth and baby food and cool.
Mix minced onion and hot water and let set for awhile until onions are soft.
Make small hamburger.
When you flip over, put a little onion on bottom.
Cut wiener buns in half.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine hash browns, soup, cheese and onion dip with 1/2 stick margarine.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine corn flakes and 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Spread on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: sweet-sour beets
directions: If you are using fresh beets, scrub well and cut off tops, leaving about an inch of stem on the beets.
Cook in boiling water until tender, 45 to 60 minutes, depending upon size and age. Drain, saving 1/3 cup cooking liquid.
Peel and dice.

title: homemade play doh
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar in a medium bowl.
Mix oil, water and coloring in small bowl.
Quickly stir liquid into dry mixture.
Dough will be stiff.
Stir all of the lumps out. When cool, store in a plastic container.

title: yum yum stir-fry beef for wok
directions: Heat about 2 tablespoons of sesame oil and begin to fry beef. Add 3 tablespoons of hoisin sauce, 1/2 cup teriyaki sauce, 1/2 cup soy sauce and hot oil to taste.
Boil Ramen noodles as directed, including seasoning packs.
When soft, add noodle and soup to beef mixture in wok.
Hot, spicy beef noodles hot pot.
Serve in bowls. Serves 3 to 4.

title: hearty hungarian goulash
directions: In Dutch oven or large saucepan, heat oil and brown beef. Drain oil.
Add Lipton soup mix and paprika, blended with tomatoes.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, for 1 1/2 hours, or until beef is tender.
Stir in flour blended with water (I make paste out of cornstarch instead of flour).
Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened, about 5 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for several hours. Serve with carrots, celery, cucumbers, zucchini, etc.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla, lemon flavoring, salt, and butter well. After mixed well add butter milk. Pour into 2-8-inch pie shell. Bake at 325° for 40 - 45 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in pan.
Put tomatoes, enchilada sauce, olives, salt and pepper all in one pot.
Add meat and onion; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: easy baked haddock, cod or pollock
directions: Season fillets to taste and coat with butter.
Roll fillets in crumbs.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 450° for 10 minutes per inch of fillet thickness.

title: creamy hot beef dip
directions: Mix ingredients in a 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly with all vegetables chopped or minced.
Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Boil, drain, then mash eggplants.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by large spoonfuls in hot oil and fry until golden.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve warm.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables according to package directions and drain.
Add cheese, mayonnaise, onion and celery.
Pour into a casserole.
Top with crackers and butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in butter in double boiler.
Break in pieces and mix with fruit and nuts.
Then combine 2 mixtures.
Mold and put in refrigerator to cool.

title: salmon puffs
directions: Need deep skillet with approximately 1 1/2 cups oil.
Heat on medium to high.
Mix all ingredients and crumble in salmon.
Put into pan by teaspoon, brown on both sides.
Eat!

title: miniature pizzas
directions: Place flattened biscuits on pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Spoon Pizza Quick sauce over biscuits (use more or less according to your liking).
Sprinkle on shredded cheese.
Add any toppings of your choice.
Bake according to temperature on back of biscuit can.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in 2 1/2-inch lengths.
Add ingredients in order listed.
Cook, covered with foil, for 20 minutes. Uncover and cook about 1 hour.

title: easy delight cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oranges, eggs and oil together for 2 minutes on medium speed mixer. Pour into 2 greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes. Cool cake completely.

title: cinnamon monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 4 pieces or roll pieces into balls.
Dip in cinnamon and sugar mix or shake in bag.
Butter Bundt pan and line with pecans.
Drop in biscuit pieces.
Melt butter; add pecans and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Slice or pull apart.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: In a pan or baking dish, cook onion slightly in oil, salt and pepper.
Cut up squash in this.
Pour tomato sauce and 1 can water over this.
Put oregano on top.
Cook on stove eye with lid on pan or dish until tender.

title: peggy's crispy candy bars
directions: Mix syrup and sugar in big saucepan. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring frequently. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter and cereal. Press mixture in well-greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Melt chocolate and butterscotch pieces in double boiler or microwave and spread over cereal mixture. Cool. Cut into 1 x 2-inch bars.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour; blend well.
Fold in nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes, until slightly browned.
Remove and cool slightly.
Roll cookies in 10x sugar while still warm.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: mocha truffle cookies
directions: In a large pan, melt margarine or butter and 1/2 cup chocolate chips over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in coffee crystals; cool 5 minutes.
Stir in sugars, eggs and vanilla.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine flour, cocoa powder, baking powder and salt; stir into coffee mixture.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Let cool 1 minute before removing from sheet.
Cool.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: garden veggie pizza squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll out crescent rolls onto a large non-stick baking sheet.
Stretch and flatten to form a single rectangular shape on the baking sheet.
Bake 11-13 minutes in the oven, or until golden brown.
Allow to cool.
Place cream cheese in a medium bowl.
Mix cream cheese with 1/2 of the ranch dressing mix.
Adjust the amount of dressing mix to taste.
Spread the mixture over the cooled crust.
Arrange carrots, red bell peppers, broccoli and green onions on top.
Chill in the refrigerator approximately 1 hour.
Cut into bite-sized squares to serve.

title: fruit nut drops
directions: Beat egg whites until almost stiff, then gradually beat in sugar until stiff.
Dredge fruit and nuts with flour and mix until coated.
Add vanilla and salt to beaten egg white, then fold in the floured fruit and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all together and roll into 2 or 3 rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.

title: cream cheese and vegetable pizza appetizer
directions: For crust, separate crescent rolls into four 4-roll rectangles and press into the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 15x10x1 inch baking pan, pressing perforations to seal. Bake in a 375 degree oven for 10-12 min. or until golden.
Cool the crust in the pan on a wire rack.
In a mixing bowl, beat together the cream cheese, mayo., and dry dressing mix until well combined.
Spread the cream cheese mixture over the cooled crust. Top with assorted vegetables and sprinkle with cheese.
Press lightly.
Cover and chill for at least 1 hour or up to 24 hours. Cut into squares to serve. Store any leftover appetizers in the refrigerator. Makes 35 servings.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually, beating after each addition, until light and airy.
Add vanilla and eggs, beat after each one.
In separate bowl, blend together cake flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix alternately in batter mixture with milk.
Beat 1 minute after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until cake begins to leave sides of the pan.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except corn flakes and melted butter. Pour in casserole dish. Top with corn flakes that have been mixed with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: yellow squash puffs
directions: Cook squash in boiling water

10 to 15 minutes or until tender; drain and mash. Combine egg and 1 cup mashed squash. Stir in dry ingredients. Add onion; mix well. Drop by tablespoon into shallow, hot oil in skillet. Cook until browned on both sides. Drain on paper towels.

title: ambrosia cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat egg with fork.
Add eggs, dry ingredients, oatmeal, then add fruit and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 dozen.

title: mashed carrots
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli-supreme
directions: Mix herb stuffing with melted butter.
Cook broccoli; drain. Combine soup, flour, sour cream, carrots, onion and seasoning. Stir in broccoli.
Put into 2-quart greased casserole.
Sprinkle stuffing mix around edge of dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This can be made ahead of time except for heating.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Mix at low speed until dough forms.
Shape dough into balls, using a rounded teaspoon of dough.
Roll balls in additional sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Top each hot cookie with a milk chocolate candy kiss, pressing down so cookie cracks around edge.

title: strawberry cake(part of the celebration of an 80th birthday; from kansas!)
directions: Mix well.
Grease and flour either a Bundt pan or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and roll in pecan bits.

title: avocado dip or guacamole salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together in order given.
Blend well; chill. Place over chunks of lettuce for a salad or use with Fritos as a dip.

title: 6 sweet crispy sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Pack in gallon jars that will seal.
Add pickling spices, pickling salt and alum.
Fill the gallon jar with cold water and vinegar.
Seal with hot lid.

title: cornstarch pudding
directions: Bring sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk to a boil.
Stir constantly and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine and vanilla.

title: peggy's bread pudding
directions: Heat milk to scalding.
Remove from heat and add butter and sugar.
Cool mixture in sink with cold water.
Add eggs, raisins and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: crock-pot smoked chicken
directions: You will need heavy-duty aluminum foil.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in butter. Stir in flour.
Add mushrooms, soup, consomme, ketchup and seasoning. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream. Heat through.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: robbie's favorite spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onion, pepper, garlic cloves and garlic powder in microwave for about 3 minutes or less.
Brown ground chuck in microwave and drain.
Place in crock-pot and add all other ingredients.
Cook on low for 4 to 5 hours.

title: cream puffs
directions: Boil water and Crisco together.
Pour flour into pan.
Stir until flour leaves the pan.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add baking powder and salt.
Let stand for 1/2 hour.
Drop spoonfuls on a greased pan spacing evenly.
Bake in oven for 10 minutes at 450°, then at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.
Fill with pudding or whipped cream.
For a richer, thicker pudding, add one envelope of Dream Whip.

title: bread pudding(microwave)
directions: Crumble bread slices into large bowl.
Add milk; soak 3 to 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and put into a microwave Bundt pan or ring and cook for 10 to 12 minutes at 70% power.
Turn halfway through cooking.

title: new york spaghetti pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Break spaghetti in half and cook in salted water until barely tender.
Drain.
Beat eggs; add Parmesan cheese and toss with warm spaghetti.
Put spaghetti mixture in greased 10-inch pie pan.
Melt butter or margarine in a medium skillet; add green pepper and onion.
Saute for 5 to 7 minutes.
Do not brown. Add sour cream to vegetables; mix and spoon over spaghetti.
Cook sausage; drain off grease.
Add tomato paste mixed with water. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Spoon tomato sauce over sour cream mixture. Bake for 25 minutes.
Cut cheese in strips and arrange over top. Return to oven for 3 to 4 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Beat eggs, sugar and salt. Add butter and syrup. Mix in pecans. Bake in pie shell 40 to 45 minutes. If adding chocolate chips, mix in with pecans.

title: chicken (sausage) casserole
directions: Brown sausage light.
Stir frequently and add onions, pepper and celery.
Cook to half done.
Add raw rice.

title: diet baked chicken
directions: The chicken sits down over the Coke can, in a sheet cake pan. Cut the triangle from its rear, rub salt and white or black pepper onto the chicken skin.
Open the can Coke and remove the tab, place the chicken over the can Coke. Pout the chicken and Coke into a sheet cake pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
If fryer is larger, it will take longer in the oven to bake, add about 15 to 30 minutes more.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Heat poultry pieces with mushroom soup.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with stuffing mix.
Bake slowly at 325° until stuffing is browned.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix and bake in 4 layers at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: cranberries (with pineapple)
directions: Cook cranberries and apples until soft in 1/2 cup water. Strain into a bowl.
Add pineapple and sugar; mix well.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup boiling water and add to mixture.
Chill until set.

title: 7-minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in top of double boiler.
Beat until blended.
Cook over boiling water, beating constantly about 7 minutes or until firm peaks form.
Remove from heat.
Beat until spreading consistency, about 2 minutes.
Add vanilla.

title: caramel marshmallows
directions: Combine milk, caramels and margarine.
Heat until melted and mixed.
Dip marshmallows in caramel and roll in Rice Krispies, coconut or chopped pecans.
Can use chocolate marshmallows.

title: banana split cake
directions: * Dip bananas in lemon juice to prevent browning.

title: bonnie's jello salad
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl and mix well.
May be served immediately or refrigerated to have later.

title: pavlova (meringue)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Add boiling water and beat on high for 7 minutes.
Mixture will be stiff and form a peak.
Put foil on baking sheet or bottom side of a round tin (9-inch size).
Put oil on foil and spread to edge. Spread meringue mixture from center to edge.
Bake in slow oven, 300°, for 1 hour exactly.
When cool, peel foil from bottom and place on dish.
Cover with whipped cream.
Add sliced fruit.

title: corn bread
directions: Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: southern pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the baking soda, in a large heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring gently, until sugar dissolves.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes to wash down sugar crystals from sides of pan.
Uncover and cook to soft ball stage (235°), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Beat with a wooden spoon just until mixture begins to thicken.
Working fast, drop by tablespoons onto greased wax paper.
Let stand until firm.
Yield: 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Place grated potatoes on a towel and wring out excess moisture. Combine all ingredients except pecans. Mix well. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with pecans. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cheesy ham and potato chowder
directions: Bring water,
vegetables,
salt
and
pepper to boil in pot. Simmer 10
minutes.
Melt
butter
in saucepan; blend in flour gradually and stir	in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Boil
1 minute. Add cheese until melted. Slowly stir cheese mixture
into vegetables.
Add ham; garnish with bacon.
Yields 6 servings.

title: turtles
directions: Bring all except pecans to a boil and boil for 12 minutes. Stir constantly; put pecans in bottom of greased pan.
Pour boiled mixture over pecans and let cool.
Cut with scissors; then dip in melted chocolate.
Makes 4 1/4 pounds candy.

title: hawaiian sweet potatoes
directions: Cook and peel potatoes; mash.
Add brown sugar, butter, salt and nutmeg.
Blend with the potatoes.
Combine pineapple and egg. Fold into potato mixture.
Pour into a well-greased (buttered) baking dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until brown. Serve plain or with Cool Whip.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs until potatoes are tender and eggs are hard-boiled. Peel potatoes and cube. Chop eggs and dice small onion. Chop the green olives, leaving 3 or 4 whole for the end. Mix all these ingredients in bowl.

title: banana loaf cake
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Sift together 3 times the flour, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture to banana mixture alternately with 1/2 cup sour milk.
(You can sour your own milk by adding one tablespoon of white vinegar.)
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Fold into mixture.
Divide batter into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until done in center.

title: baked caramel popcorn
directions: Melt slowly all ingredients except popcorn and soda, then boil 5 minutes.
Add soda.
Pour over popcorn. Put on 2 cookie sheets. Bake 1/2 hour in 225° oven, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions
in butter; mix with soup.
Line bottom of casserole
with
saltines.
Pour
soup
and onion mixture over saltines.
Mix eggs and
milk
with
salt
and pepper and pour over soup and onion
mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: mocha fudge sauce(low-fat recipe)
directions: Combine margarine and chocolate in a small pan.
Cook on low until chocolate melts.
Combine sugar and next three ingredients in a small bowl.
Add corn syrup and milk.
Stir with wire whisk until blended.
Add to saucepan.

title: excellent barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a saucepan.
Simmer over low flame until mixture comes to a boil, stirring frequently.
Let boil for 1 minute; remove from heat.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Beat eggs and sugar; gradually drizzle
chocolate mix.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to chocolate mix.
Stir in nuts.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Make 1-inch balls; roll in powdered sugar.
Grease cookie sheets.
Bake at 300 degrees for 15 to 18 minutes.
Put on wire racks to cool.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Prepare sauce by combining all ingredients except cornstarch. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch, diluted in a little water.
Saute chicken in a little oil (do not brown).
Add all other ingredients and stir constantly.
Add sweet and sour sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6.

title: caviar chicken kiev
directions: Cut each boned chicken breast in 2 pieces.
Remove skins. Pound with flat cleaver until thin.
Place 1 teaspoon of caviar on top of butter.
Roll up breasts and tie with thread.
Beat eggs. Roll chicken in egg and then bread crumbs.
Fry them in deep fat at 370°.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for chocolate chips. Spread mixture in a a 9 by 13 inch pan, making sure to flattened mixture. Use double boiler to melt chocolate chips, spread on top. Cut into squares before refrigerating.
Tastes like peanut butter cups.
Great recipe!
No baking!

title: cock-eyed cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, sugar and salt onto a greased square cake pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Make 3 grooves or holes in the dry mixture. Pour into one hole oil, next hole, pour vinegar, next hole vanilla.
Then pour water over it all.
Beat with a spoon until nearly smooth and you cannot see the flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix tomato soup, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Layer carrots, onion rings, and bell pepper slices.
Cover with sauce.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Mixture may be replenished by adding carrots, onions, and bell peppers as they are used.
By being kept covered in the refrigerator, sauce may be kept for a month.

title: "moose juice" punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot tea.
Add orange juice and lemon juice. Chill for 2 hours.
Prior to serving, add 2 quarts of ginger ale. Serve on ice.

title: punch
directions: Simmer the sugar and water together for 10 minutes.
Let cool. Add the juices.
When ready to serve, add the ginger ale.

title: apple bread
directions: Cook apples; add no sugar. Cook until done and mash.

title: carrot cake #1
directions: Beat eggs until well blended.
Add oil and sugar.
Beat after each addition. Add all dry ingredients to oil mixture. Add carrots, pineapple and nuts. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 4 (7-inch) layers (enough for 2 cakes).

title: onion pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with 1/2 stick melted butter.
Press into an 8-inch pie plate.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons of butter until clear, but not brown.
Spoon into crust.
Beat eggs together with milk, salt and pepper and pour over onions.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spinach fantastic
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Press spinach between paper towels to remove excess water.
Combine rice, spinach and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart shallow casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: french baked potatoes
directions: Wash and quarter potatoes; leave skins on.
Dry potato quarters and soak in vegetable oil for approximately 1 minute. One at a time, dip potatoes in seasoned bread crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes or until fork goes in easily.
Serve and top with your favorite topping.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to a boil.
Add jello and simmer. Set aside and cool.

title: castleton tuna mac salad
directions: Mix tuna, macaroni, peas, onion, celery and salt.
Mix mayonnaise and yogurt.
Stir into tuna mixture.

title: macaroni bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Cook macaroni as label directs.
Drain well.
In casserole, stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: layered potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water about 30 minutes or until tender; drain and cool slightly.
Peel and thinly slice potatoes; set aside.
Combine parsley and onion and set aside.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, celery seed, salt and pepper and horseradish; stir well.
Place 1/3 of potatoes in a 13 x 9-inch dish; top with 1/3 mayonnaise mixture, 1/3 sliced eggs and 1/3 of onion and parsley mixture.
Repeat layers twice.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir together flour and baking powder. Blend with caramel mixture. Stir in nuts and Heath bars. Bake in greased pan for 25 minutes. Bake at 350°. Makes 4 dozen.

title: bubble bread
directions: Mix pudding and sugar.
Spray pan with Pam.
Put rolls in bottom of pan.
Put pudding and brown sugar over rolls.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Melt butter and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by level tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
1 1/2 dozen.

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft.
Stir in corned beef and ketchup. Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, approximately 15 minutes. Serve in hot, split buns. Makes 8 sandwiches.
Serve these with hot vegetable soup.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Peel and core apples, then slice. Combine sugar, flour and spices in a cup. Sprinkle over sliced apples and toss until well coated. Spoon into pastry shell.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices in large bowl.
Set aside.
Combine salad oil, sugar, egg yolks and hot water in bowl.
Mix well.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour the contents of this bowl over dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in grated carrots.
Fold in separately beaten egg whites.
Turn batter into a well-greased and lightly floured loaf or angel food pan .
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool and serve with hard sauce, if desired, or sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Will keep well if wrapped in foil and refrigerated.

title: high flying biscuits
directions: In a medium bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt together. With a fork, blend in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in milk until well blended.
Drop biscuit-size spoonfuls of dough onto a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: split pea and ham soup
directions: Place peas in water; soak overnight. Cook carrots and onions for 10 minutes or until soft; add to peas. Add thyme, bay leaf, salt and ham bone. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer about 2 hours. Remove bone. Can put in blender. Then add sugar and butter.

title: lemon-orange cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 (8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inch) layer pans as directed on package.
Cool.
Split to make 4 layers.
Reserve 1 tablespoon orange juice concentrate for glaze.
Fill layers with remaining concentrate using 3 tablespoons between each layer.
Mix reserved 1 tablespoon concentrate, the butter and confectioners sugar.
Spread over top of cake.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients except cereal, then add cereal.
Make into balls or flatten.
Put on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: crab meat spread
directions: On serving platter (silver is nice), spread softened cheese. Top with chili sauce, garlic powder and crab meat.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve on crackers or pumpernickel bread.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Drain can of whole kernel corn.
Blend all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Test with knife in center for doneness.

title: chinese spiders
directions: Melt chips together.
Add nuts and noodles. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Refrigerate until set up.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all together.
Garnish with a cup of ripe tomatoes.

title: hot cinnamon twisties
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Open biscuits and flatten each one.
Cut slit from the edge to the center of each biscuit.
Dip each in melted butter, then in sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Pull, then twist each biscuit, place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: special "k" bars
directions: Heat sugar and syrup just until sugar melts.
Add peanut butter and cereal.
Firmly pack into a 10 x 10-inch (or 9 x 13-inch for thinner) greased pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in a double boiler or on Medium power in the microwave.
Spread over Special "K" mix.
Cut after setting.

title: pepperoni pizza snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Spray 8 in. square pan with non-stick cooking spray.
Remove dough from can.
Unroll dough, separate into strips.
