Cut each strip in half crosswise to make 20 pieces.
Press each piece to form 2 1/2 in. squares.
Top each square with 1 slice pepperoni and 1 cheese cube.
Wrap dough around filling to completely cover; firmly press edges to seal. Place butter mixture from breadstick package into small microwave safe bowl.
Microwave on high for 10-20 seconds or until melted. Dip each filled dough bite into melted butter.
Place seam side down with sides touching in sprayed pan.
Bake qt 400 degrees 15-20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Serve warm sticks with warm pizza sauce.
You may use marinara sauce to replace pizza sauce.

title: fruit bowl
directions: In a large bowl, empty pineapple and peaches with their juices.
Add sliced bananas, cubed apples, sliced kiwi and cubed oranges.
Sprinkle sugar over fruit and stir.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into long Pyrex dish.
Freeze.
Let set out of freezer 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into a large bowl. Make a well in dry ingredients and add eggs one at a time and beat.
Add remaining ingredients to first mixture; mix thoroughly and pour into greased, floured pans 1/2 full.
(Makes 3 loaf pans or 3 large coffee cans.)

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt the marshmallows and margarine in the top of a double boiler or over very low heat until melted.
Stir in vanilla and food coloring to tint to the desired shade of green.
Combine marshmallow mixture and corn flakes.
Stir to mix all flakes with the marshmallow mixture.
Stir carefully so not to break the flakes.
Drop by heaping tablespoons on buttered foil.
Then shape into wreaths, using your fingers dipped into cold water so it is easier to shape.
Decorate with red hots or decorations to make Christmas wreaths.

title: eggplant balls
directions: Heat
oil
and
saute
garlic.
Add
diced eggplant and water and cover.
Cook until eggplant is soft.
In mixing bowl combine eggplant, bread crumbs, parsley, eggs and cheese.
Mix well and let stand for
minutes.
Form into balls and fry, or bake on greased pan
for 30 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: orange nut coffee cake
directions: Sift into a bowl the 7 dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk, oil, orange juice and rind.
Beat with mixer on medium speed just until mixed.
When mixed, pour into oiled and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8-inch round pans.
Combine topping.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and bell pepper until done.
Pour in a casserole dish, add the beans.
Mix in ketchup and brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in oven or microwave for 18 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour pineapple into casserole dish and cover with grated cheese.
Mix juice (about half of amount saved) from pineapple with flour and sugar. Pour over pineapple and cheese.
Mix melted margarine and cracker crumbs and top casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place ingredients in layers in a 2-quart baking dish with a tight fitting lid.

title: espresso chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Position rack in center of oven.
Preheat oven to 400°. Grind wafer cookies; add butter and mix until crumbs are moist. Press crumbs on bottom and 1 1/2 inches up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Wrap outside of pan with aluminum foil.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over 1 cup quick oats and let stand 30 minutes.
Cream the butter and brown and white sugar together.
Add well beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Then add to oatmeal mixture.
Next add the flour, cinnamon, soda and salt. Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: velvet fudge cake
directions: Chop almonds and toast at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and milk and beat well.
Add the flour, cornmeal, lemon juice and grated rind.
Pour mixture into two pastry-lined pie plates and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until crust and filling are done.
This makes 2 pies.

title: strawberry cookie cake
directions: Mix all together and pat out on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for about 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Cut in squares while still warm.
Serve with strawberries and whipped cream.

title: open house punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix in punch bowl (7-Up last).
Stir.
Add a floating ring of ice.

title: squash bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine both sugars, cooked squash, cooking oil and eggs.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in water. Thoroughly stir together flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger.
Add to squash mixture and mix well.

title: macaroni loaf
directions: Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagne turkey
directions: Roll turkey breast in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil. Drain on paper towel, then place in baking dish.
Cover meat with spaghetti sauce, then cover.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Remove cover and place cheese on top of each piece of turkey, may have to cut cheese into small pieces.
Best served with fresh broccoli, homemade rolls and spaghetti.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in an ungreased baking dish.
Cover and bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes until rice is done.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish and layer ingredients in the following order:
chicken, broccoli, rice, cheese and soup.
Repeat layers in the same order except the top layer should end with cheese. Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: o' susannah pie
directions: In bowl or oblong pan, break 1 pie shell into pieces; set aside. Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add lemon juice. Beat. Fold in condensed milk, then fold in Cool Whip. Pour 1/2 of this over broken pie shell. Put about 1/2 cup or more Bits 'o Brickle over this, then drizzle caramel sauce over, starting with your 2nd broken pie crust. Do another layer, ending with caramel sauce. Chill.

title: hot cheese tacos
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Pour off fat.
Add the package of taco seasoning mix.
Pour in tomato sauce and water.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Spoon mixture into unbaked taco shells.
Put sliced cheese on top; whatever amount you like.
Put in 400° oven until cheese has melted.
Top with lettuce or lettuce and tomatoes.
Add hot or mild taco sauce.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Clean whole chicken.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Melt margarine in frying pan.
Brown chicken on all four sides.
After browned, put whole chicken in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup parsley flakes.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 cup water.
Pour water into pan with chicken drippings.
Stir and pour stock over chicken in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 4 to 6 hours. After cooked remove chicken and thicken gravy with flour.
This is good served over rice.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, cheese and pineapple.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Spread crackers on top.
Pour melted butter over crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: reduced-fat kentucky chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan mix egg yolks, sugar and cocoa, then add milk. Cook and stir until very thick.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Beat in 1 tablespoon sugar. Beat until stiff.
Spread over filling.
Broil for 1 minute, watching carefully until meringue is light golden brown.
Chill.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, condensed milk and Key lime juice in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 160° (about 10 minutes).
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar at high speed of electric mixer until foamy. Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Pour hot filling into pastry shell.
Immediately spread meringue over filling, sealing to edge.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Saute onions until light brown.
Add potatoes, carrots, water, salt, pepper and dill weed. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir in
milk and parsley and heat until hot.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and discard meat.
Saute green pepper, onion and garlic in drippings until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except rice.
Simmer 5 minutes until heated through. Serve over rice.

title: lemon crackers
directions: Stir ammonia in 1/4 cup warm water.
Allow to stand until softened.
Cream the shortening and sugar until well blended.
Add beaten eggs; blend well.
Add salt and lemon oil.
Add ammonia to milk and mix alternately with flour to first mixture until mixture is of proper consistency to handle.
Press out on well-floured board with hands.
Cut in squares or circles.
Bake in 400° oven until
light brown.

title: white chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Melt butter. Add sugar and blend. Blend in eggs, salt and vanilla. Blend in flour and melted white chocolate.
Pour in 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: darn good cake
directions: Mix cake mix, dry pudding, eggs, oil, water and flavorings. Beat well.

title: fiesta
directions: Brown the hamburger.
Add to the hamburger the taco sauce, tomato paste or sauce and Prego sauce.
Add a little water if too thick.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Layer the crushed corn chips, cooked rice and the hamburger mixture.
Top with chopped lettuce, green peppers, tomatoes, mushrooms and onions.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and pecans.
This is best layered on individual serving plates or bowls.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat together first 7 ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together last 4 ingredients and spread on top of sweet potato mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Mix well.
Knead until dough is formed.
Press into cookie sheet and prick with fork.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes. Cut into strips while still warm.

title: fruit whip pie
directions: Put fruit pulp through coarse strainer.
Add sugar, nuts and egg whites (beaten stiff).
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 20 minutes in slow oven (300°).
Cool and cover with whipped cream.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Marinate beef, chicken or shrimp overnight.
Baste with sauce while grilling.
Can add sesame seed.

title: orange coconut delights
directions: Combine vanilla wafers and walnuts in processor or blender and chop finely.
Mix powdered sugar, butter and orange juice concentrate in medium bowl.
Add to cookie crumbs and process until blended.
Form mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Serve at room temperature.
Store cookies in fridge.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: dublin's finest caramel apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan over low heat, combine brown sugar, butter and 2 tablespoons whipping cream.
Cook and stir just until butter is melted.
Remove from heat; stir in pecans.
Pour mixture into bottom of ungreased 9-inch round or 9-inch square cake pan and set aside.
In large bowl, combine bread mix, apple, water, oil and egg.
Stir 50 to 75 strokes by hand until mix is moistened.
Carefully spoon batter over caramel mixture, making sure caramel is completely covered.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 1 minute; invert onto serving plate.
Cool.

title: baked carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble over drained carrots in casserole dish.
Add diced onions, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Pour melted butter mixture over carrots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Stir occasionally.

title: skillet barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown chops slowly in hot oil on both sides; drain.
Combine 1/2 cup of water with next 3 ingredients.
Pour over chops.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Turn chops over and cook 30 minutes longer.
Remove from pan.
Dissolve cornstarch in remaining water. Stir into pan.
Cook until sauce boils and thickens.
Return chops and coat both sides with sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: herbed roasted potatoes
directions: Brush large baking dish with olive oil.
Add diced potatoes. Sprinkle with spices.
Add onion and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: excellent meat loaf
directions: Combine all of the ingredients except 1/2 of the tomato sauce. Mix well.
Place in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cook at 350° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour off excess fat.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over loaf.
Return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable cheese soup(serves 12)
directions: Cook water, bouillon, potatoes, celery and onion for 15 minutes.
Add the broccoli, cauliflower and mixed vegetables. Cook 15 minutes.
Add soup and water.
Heat thoroughly.
Add cheese and heat until melted.
Do not boil.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Beat together margarine, eggs, sugar, sour cream and vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt and add to mixture.
Put half of mixture into Bundt pan which has been well greased and floured.
Mix together the cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts. Sprinkle on top of batter.
Then add remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: betty lou's cracker jacks
directions: Bring sugar, Karo, margarine and salt to a boil. When it boils, cook 5 minutes.
Turn down.
Add baking soda and vanilla. After it comes off stove, pour over corn and bake 45 minutes at 250°.
Keep popcorn warm before baking. Store in airtight container.

title: auntie nancy's homemade applesauce
directions: Core, peel and slice apples.
Put in 4-quart pan.
Add water, sugar and cinnamon.
Simmer on low heat until desired consistency, stirring occasionally.

title: easy hearty vegetable beef stew
directions: Cook stew meat.
Boil hard until tender; drain.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
In a large cooker combine all the ingredients. Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add 2 cans of vegetable soup and meat.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: apple torte
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar.
Mix in eggs, then stir in flour.
Spread into greased 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch pan.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Mix with 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, or more to taste.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place ribs in shallow roasting pan, meaty sides up.
On each piece, place a slice of unpeeled lemon and a thin slice of onion. Roast in 450° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve sugar and gelatin in boiling water. Chill until thickened, but not firm. Add all remaining ingredients, mixing well until sour cream disappears. Top with walnuts, if desired. Chill until firm.

title: dilah (easter bread)
directions: Mix warm water, 1 Tbsp. sugar and yeast together.
Set aside to let mixture rise.
Mix together eggs, 1 c. sugar, vanilla, oil, butter, and warm milk in bowl.
Add risen yeast to mix.
Start adding flour until you can handle dough.
Cut dough in half.
Form two rings and lay on pans.
Let rise until it doubles in size. Bake at 250 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.
For topping, mix together 10 X sugar and butter.
Spread on top.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix everything together, except soup and water.
Make balls at least 2 inches in diameter.
Place in baking dish.
Pour soup and water over it.
Bake, covered, at 350° for one and one-half hours. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta to al dente stage.
Do not overcook.
Drain.
Pour on Italian dressing and cool.
Add the remaining ingredients. Stir together and serve.

title: bananas foster
directions: Melt butter in a heavy skillet.
Add sugar; stir until melted. Add rest of ingredients.
Cook briefly.
Serve over vanilla ice cream.
Sprinkle walnut pieces on top.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut cooled eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks.
Put yolks in a bowl with other ingredients.
Fill egg whites with mixture; sprinkle with paprika.
Cool and serve.

title: turkey  sloppy joes
directions: In a nonstick skillet, cook turkey and onions for 5 minutes or until turkey is no longer pink. Add the next 7 ingredients, simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve on buns; yields 6 servings.

title: california pasta salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a large bowl; cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.
Yields 10 to 15 servings.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve red jello in 3/4 cup hot water; add 1 cup cold water. Pour into mold and let set.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up cauliflower, broccoli, chopped celery, carrots and onions.
Pour dressing on it and refrigerate.
This is better if made the night before using.
You may also use Ranch dressing.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Cook onions over lowest heat until limp but not brown.
Add beef stock, salt and pepper. Simmer 15 minutes over medium heat.
Puree hot soup in batches in a blender or processor.
Heat butter or oil in skillet; brown bread on both sides.
Combine egg yolks and Port wine in bowl; reserve.
Place 1 slice of bread in each of 6 bowls; pour soup and sprinkle cheese over.
Place under preheated broiler for 1 minute or until cheese is melted and slightly brown.
Cut crust of cheese with a tablespoon and pour in 1/4 cup of egg mixture.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into refrigerator and chill well. Take out and roll in a
ball;
then roll in dried parsley.	Spread on crackers.

title: cocktail cheese crackers
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese; add margarine.
Work together well with fingers.
Add flour.
Work well after each step.
Add Rice Krispies.
Form into small balls about the size of large walnuts. Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with fork.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned at 325°.

title: hot pockets
directions: Divide dough into 24 balls.
Roll each out into a circle. Fill with mixture of chicken, cream cheese and green onions or turkey ham and cheese.
Fold over edges and seal.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
For ham and cheese hot pockets, dip in fat free pizza sauce (heated).

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all together, putting nuts in the bottom of pan.
Pour batter in pan over nuts and bake at 350° for 55 minutes until done.

title: corn bread
directions: Set oven at 425°.
Place shortening in an 8 x 8-inch pan and let it melt while you assemble the rest of the ingredients.

title: lemonade fruit salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs in top of double boiler. Stir in sugar and lemonade concentrate. Cook and stir over simmering water until thick. Cool thoroughly. Fold in whipped cream. Chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs to milk.
Add this mixture to sugar and flour mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add vanilla and remove from heat.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding in bowl.

title: potato casserole
directions: Blend cream cheese into hot mashed potatoes.
Add egg, chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: rick's special spaghetti
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add salt, pepper, onion and mushrooms. Simmer couple of minutes.
Add Worcestershire sauce and let meat soak up, then add Ragu.
Prepare noodles as directed on box.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Grease a 12 x 2-inch round pan.
Press dough halfway up sides of pan.
Cover with towel; let rise for 20 to 30 minutes or until almost doubled in bulk.

title: cherokee cranberry relish
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: easy cookie bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pat mixture, except 1 cup, into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach cottage cheese casserole
directions: Grease 1 quart casserole.
Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Add to casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: stuffed hamburgers
directions: Mix ground beef and salt.
Divide into 12 equal parts (12 patties) and flatten to about 5 inches in diameter.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Divide among 6 patties.
Top each pattie with stuffing mixture (6 of them).
Place remaining meat patties on top and press edges together with a fork.
Barbecue or broil for 20 minutes, turning once.
Serves 6.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until very stiff.
Fold in first 3 ingredients and put into crust.
Cover with Cool Whip and chill.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add flour and water, then vanilla and nuts.
Grease cookie sheet and form dough into crescents.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar when taken from oven.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix this real good and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool completely.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients. Add apples last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Leave cake in pan after baking, or turn out on plate.
Punch knife holes in cake and ice it.

title: pasta buffet with alfredo sauce
directions: Cook spaghetti
in boiling, salted water with a little olive oil.
Rinse in hot water and put in large bowl.
Let everyone build their plate of pasta, creating their own salad on top. Serve with garlic bread sticks for a fantastic meal.

title: bourbon pie
directions: Combine marshmallows and canned milk in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until all the marshmallows have melted.
Chill completely.
Whip cream and fold in marshmallow mixture and bourbon.
Pour into pie shell and chill 4 to 6 hours.

title: do not stir peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x
13-inch
Pyrex dish.
Make a batter with sugar, flour, baking
powder
and
salt.
Mix
with milk. Pour batter into dish with
melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour fruit over this again; do not stir.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar on top.
Do not stir.
Bake in
oven
for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm with Cool Whip.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, reserved crab meat liquid, onion, lemon juice, salt and pepper sauce.
Stir in crab meat.
Turn into greased shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot!!! Enjoy!!!

title: beet wine
directions: Boil beets 1/2 hour in 3 quarts of water, strain and add enough water to make 1 1/2 gallons.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Let stand 9 to 12 days, strain.
Let stand until clear.
Put in bottles and seal.
It's good!

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix and fry meatballs.
Saute onions in small pan.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix according to directions. Form into balls. Roll balls in a mix of cinnamon and sugar. Flatten only enough to prevent rolling on cookie sheet. Bake according to package instructions.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese and dressing.
Mix along with margarine together.
Shape into ball and cover with nuts.

title: chicken in the crock-pot
directions: Place oleo in bottom of crock-pot.
Add cut-up fryer, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes, bell pepper and onion.
Pour soup over mixture.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Place lid on crock-pot and cook on low for 8 hours or on high for 5 hours.

title: chicken biscuit stew
directions: In 10-inch skillet, melt margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth and milk.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add chicken, onion, peas and carrots.
Simmer until hot and bubbly.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Bake biscuits according to can.
Serves 4. You can also make Bisquick biscuits.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into crust.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: drumstick pie
directions: Mix flour, oleo and half the nuts together.
Mix well and pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Cool well.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix chocolate pudding according to directions on box. Spread over cream cheese. Top with layer of Cool Whip. Sprinkle 1/2 of the nuts over top.
Refrigerate. Will serve 12 to 14.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Wash strawberries and mix sugar and cornstarch in 3-quart saucepan.
Stir in water and mashed berries.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in food coloring.
Cool.
Fold remaining 2 pints berries into cooled mixture.
Pile into pie shell and chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cheese biscuits(servings:  4)
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Beat eggs lightly and add to milk and butter.
Add liquid to dry ingredients and mix until smooth.
Pour mixture into well buttered cups a little more than half full.
Place on cookie sheet and place in cold oven.
Turn oven on to 425° and bake for 1 hour.
Makes about 8, depending upon the size of your cups.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together sugar, cornstarch, oleo and eggs.
Add buttermilk, lemon extract, almond extract and salt.
Pour into pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Turn down to 350° and bake until golden brown.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook the macaroni until it is tender in salted water.
Put it into a casserole dish.
Add the milk, cheese, pepper to taste and dot it with butter.
Top the macaroni with bread crumbs and bake it for about 30 minutes at 325° to 350° or until brown.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Slice onion ahead of time and put in ice water for 20 minutes. Remove from water and pat dry.
Put in batter and then fry in hot oil until brown, then put on paper towels to drain.

title: 90 minute yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast (each packet of granule yeast is 1/2 ounce or 1 tablespoon) in 1 cup of warm water.
Mix in rest of ingredients until dough is soft, but not sticky.
Use all whole wheat flour, if desired, or all white or you can divide equally.
When dough is soft and leaves sides of bowl, cut into 4 pieces.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Pound with rolling pin for 1 minute each piece of dough on lightly floured board.
Form into loaves and put into 4 greased pans.
Let stand 30 minutes or until double in size.
Bake 20-30 minutes at 350°.
When done cool on rack before removing loaves.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix well with mixer and pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: jean's caramels
directions: Cook all the ingredients, except the vanilla, to a hard boil. Stir occasionally to prevent burning.
When mixture has reached hard-ball stage, remove from heat and stir in the vanilla.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Cool and then cut to desired size pieces.

title: french onion soup
directions: Pour bouillon in crock-pot.
Cook onions slowly in a large skillet in butter.
Cover and let cook for about 15 minutes. Uncover and add salt and flour (and sugar).
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours (high 3 hours).
Before serving, top with grated cheese. Recipe maybe doubled for a 5-quart crock-pot.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
60 Spinach Balls.

title: sausage lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions; Drain noodles.
Rinse with cool water; Drain again.

title: quick chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, oil, vanilla and egg in large bowl with spoon until smooth.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Divide dough into halves.

Shape one half into 2 strips, about 15 x 3-inches, about 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle each strip with chocolate chips and nuts; press lightly. Bake until golden brown, 7 to 9 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes.
Cut each strip crosswise into 1-inch slices; remove from cookie sheet. Repeat with remaining half dough.
Store loosely covered.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: old fashioned soft pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine, flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in medium bowl.
Cream butter and sugar in large mixer bowl.
Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla; beat until light and creamy.
Mix in dry ingredients until well blended.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Smooth tops of cookies.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on wire racks. Drizzle Glaze over tops.

title: fast and fabulous fruit
directions: Combine pudding mix and fruit with juice in a bowl.
With electric mixer at low speed, beat until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Blend in whipped topping.
Spoon into individual dessert dishes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs about 5 minutes or until golden.
Add sugar and beat until almost smooth.
Add vanilla, fruit and cream, stir.
Pour into freezer and add milk until 3/4 full.
Put freezer in ice cream maker and follow manufacturer's instructions.

title: butter nut chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and butter flavor Crisco until creamy.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix together.
Stir in nuts (mixture will be stiff).
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is light brown.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: miniature meat turnovers
directions: In skillet, brown the first five ingredients.
Separate rolls as directed, then cut triangles in half.
Place spoon of mixture on dough and fold over, sealing edges.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: lemon cream cheese pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water, mixing until smooth. Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thickened and clear.
Quickly stir in egg yolks and bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in 1/3 cup lemon juice, salt and oleo.
Cool for several hours or overnight.
In a bowl, blend Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese until smooth; stir in pudding and remaining lemon juice. Fold into chilled lemon filling.
Divide and spoon into baked pie shells.
Chill several hours.
Garnish with whipped cream and lemon slices.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Saute chicken, onions and garlic in oil until lightly brown. Bring cornstarch and broth to boil stirring constantly.
Cook 1 minute more.
Remove from heat, add 1 cup cheese, salad dressing, sour cream, chilies, 1/4 cup of olives.

title: winter strawberries
directions: Grind together (food processor or blender) the apples and cranberries.
Add pineapple and sugar.
Let stand at least 2 hours before using.
Keep refrigerated and it will keep a long time. Good on toast, waffles, shortcake or angel food cake.

title: pork steak vegetable bake
directions: Place potatoes and carrots in bottom of an 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch dish.
Trim fat from steaks.
In large skillet, cook trimmings until there are about 2 tablespoons oil; discard trimmings.
In hot oil, brown steaks well on both sides.
In a small pan, combine water, onion soup mix and soy sauce; bring to boiling.
Spoon half soup mix over potatoes and carrots; top with steaks.
Spoon remaining soup mixture over steaks.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more. Makes 4 servings.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Sprinkle cayenne pepper (lightly).
Add as much Blue cheese as you like.

title: magic coconut bars
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan; mix melted butter with crumbs to make crust.
Pour in milk; mix remaining ingredients and pour over milk.
Press gently to settle ingredients.	Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place meatballs in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and pour the cranberry/chili sauce mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: string bean salad
directions: Cook green beans in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Add onion, oil and vinegar dressing, salt and pepper to taste.

title: pork chops mexican style
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Pour Mexicorn on top (including liquid); cover skillet and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes. Place one tomato on top of corn (per chop) and simmer for 15 minutes longer.
Great one dish meal.

title: chicken dressing for large family
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough chicken broth for desired consistency.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer shredded cabbage, sliced velveeta and crumbled crackers.
Layer same again.
Top with cup of milk.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350° or until cabbage is tender. Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix bread, milk, hamburger and 1/4 cup onions together.
Shape into round balls and place in baking dish.
Mix all the remaining ingredients together and pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 16 to 20 meat balls.

title: mustard vinaigrette
directions: Place mustard, garlic, spices and vinegar in small bowl. Whisk until thoroughly blended.
Slowly add olive oil, stirring constantly until ingredients combine.
Add sugar and adjust to taste.
Add cheese and mix together.
Serve over salad greens.

title: toasted-buttered pecans
directions: Spread pecans evenly in a shallow pan.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Dot with oleo.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°, stirring frequently.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach only long enough until you can pull it apart with a fork.
Drain off liquid.
Mix other ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour this mixture into the spinach and stir thoroughly. Cook on low about 30 minutes or until set.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Fry ground beef; drain grease.
Remove from heat and stir in cottage cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Spread small amount in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put one layer of uncooked lasagna noodles across entire pan.
Spread 1/2 of meat mixture over noodles. Sprinkle 1/2 of each cheese over meat mixture.
Repeat layers one more time (noodles, meat mixture with cheese on top).
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in butter.
Add to peas with cream of chicken or mushroom soup.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken and sour cream enchiladas
directions: Save broth from cooking chicken and keep hot.
For cooked sauce, combine onion, garlic and butter in heavy saucepan.
Cook until soft, not brown. Add tomatoes, chilies, sugar, cumin, oregano and basil.
In a large bowl, mix soup, milk and sour cream. To soften tortillas, dip one at a time in hot chicken broth.

To fix enchiladas, place thin layers of chicken, cooked sauce, cheese and a spoonful of creamed mixture onto flour tortillas. Roll up enchiladas and put in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan or baking dish.
Pour remaining sour cream mixture over enchiladas.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baton rouge fire department pork roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season all sides of roast very well with Cajun seasoning, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Put roast in open pan (fat side up so that it will melt down over roast) with 1/2-inch of water added to pan.
Allow 30 minutes cooking time for each pound of meat.
Cook 1 hour, then cover with foil and cook for remainder of allotted time.
(Keep water level consistent in pan, adding water as needed.)
After roast is covered with foil and has "roasted" 2 1/2 to 3 hours, check the level of water again and continue to cook one more hour.
Remove from oven and let rest for 10 minutes before carving.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together.
Pour into buttered baking dish.

title: sue's barbecued ribs(best ever ribs)
directions: Sprinkle ribs with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Place in shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes; pour off fat. Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Reduce oven to 350°. Brush ribs with sauce and continue baking 1 hour, basting once or twice with sauce.
Turn once during baking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: red chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken until tender in 4 cups of water.
Cut into pieces.

title: figgy pudding cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients; add next 2.
Slowly add last 4 ingredients; blend well.
Pour into greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
May require longer in a Bundt pan. Serve plain or drizzled with powdered sugar icing.

title: mississippi cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.

title: pantry cheese bread
directions: Bring to room temperature.
Whip slowly with mixer until fluffy.
Butter sourdough bread and toast under broiler.
Enjoy!

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook beef and onion until brown; drain and put in bottom of 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread sweet peas and corn over ground beef.
Spread soup over vegetables. Cream potatoes with milk and egg; season with salt and pepper. Spoon over other mix; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
(May use instant potatoes.)

title: cheese ball (old english)
directions: Mix cream, English and Blue cheese well; add vinegar and garlic to taste.

title: grape salad
directions: Cook until well coated (not runny); let stand until cool. Put on top of grape mixture or put chopped pecans.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shells, in a large bowl.
Pour into pie shells and refrigerate.

title: french potato salad with bacon
directions: Serves 4 to 6. Takes 30 minutes to prepare.
Quarter potatoes and boil in salted water 8 to 10 minutes until tender but still firm.
Chop bacon and saute until crisp.
Remove bacon and saute scallions in fat.
When potatoes are done, drain them and put into large bowl.
While hot, pour over them the vinegars, olive oil, salt, pepper and scallions.
Toss to coat.
Add red onion and parsley; toss again.
Add bacon.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix milk, egg yolks, sugar, cocoa and flour.
Cook in large microwave bowl, covered on High for 2 minutes; stir well with a whisk, cook additional 2 minutes intervals until thick, approximately 6 minutes.
Add vanilla and margarine; cool slightly, pour into crust, top with whipped egg whites.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: holly wreaths
directions: Cream the shortening, cream cheese and sugar well.
Beat in vanilla. Gradually blend in flour. Fill press.
Form cookies on ungreased cookie sheet. Form wreaths going in circular motion. Gently press ends of wreaths together.
Bake.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: bisticks
directions: Roll each biscuit between palms of hands to pencil-thin strips.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Brush with egg white. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lucy's pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat until cake dough turns golden color and is fluffy (3 to 4 minutes).
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake in Bundt pan 50 to 60 minutes.
This cake does not need icing.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together; sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: coconut ice cream
directions: Peel the brown skin off the back and grate (by hand or in blender) with some of the water.
Strain and squeeze to extract coconut milk.
Blend custard powder or cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water.
Bring 1/2 cup water to boil.
Add custard paste and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil until color darkens.
Remove from fire.
Cool slightly.
Add coconut milk. Sieve custard.
Add condensed
and evaporated milk.
Add essence last.
Freeze.
(You may churn in ice crem freezer for a creamy texture.)

title: new york cheese cake(light version)
directions: Mix at medium speed until well blended.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned, about 30 minutes.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain off fat.
Add celery; cook 10 minutes. Stir often.
Add 2 pints water.
Add other ingredients and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Serve with cornbread.

title: spinach dip bread bowl
directions: Mix salad dressing, sour cream and Ranch mix until well blended.

Add spinach, water chestnuts and red peppers; mix well. Refrigerate. Cut slice from top of bread loaf. Remove center leaving 1-inch thick shell. Cut removed bread into bite-size pieces. Spoon dip into bread loaf just before serving. Serve with dippers and bread pieces. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: surprise apple salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Refrigerate until serving. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: quickie dewberry cobbler
directions: In the bottom of a baking pan or dish, melt the margarine. Add milk, but do not stir it.
Sift the dry ingredients together and then into the dish.
Do not stir this either.
Add the dewberries.
Bake at 325° to 350° until crust rises to top and browns.

title: trillionaire candy
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine caramel topping and pecans over medium heat.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil and cook 3 to 5 minutes longer or until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and allow to cool 5 minutes. Spoon about 1 1/2 teaspoons caramel mixture on top of each cracker.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm. In a small saucepan, melt chocolate chips over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Using tongs, dip bottom of each cracker in chocolate. Transfer to waxed paper and refrigerate 1 hour or until chocolate is firm. Store in an
airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions and green pepper in butter.
Add soup and cream.
Stir until smooth.
Set aside.
Butter a 13-inch oblong pan.
Layer with half the noodles.
Place half the chicken in the pan, top with half the cheeses and pour half the sauce over the cheeses.
Repeat layers with other half of ingredients, ending with sauce.
Sprinkle with saved Mozzarella and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: pudding-wiches
directions: Add milk gradually to peanut butter in a deep narrow bowl, blending until smooth.
Add pudding mix and beat on low speed for 2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Spread filling 1/2 -inch thick on 12 of the crackers.
Top with remaining crackers, making into sandwiches.
Freeze until firm (approx. 3 hours).
Makes 12.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in pineapple, sour cream and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Place egg yolks in a small bowl and beat slightly; stir in small amount of hot pineapple mixture until well blended. Return yolk mixture to saucepan.
Stirring constantly, cook 2 minutes more.
Cool mixture slightly and spoon into pastry shell. Cool completely; then top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Combine sugar, vanilla and eggs in large bowl.
Blend well. Blend in flour.
Heat milk in pan until hot.
Add butter to milk and add this to batter.
Beat well.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and frost with following icing.

title: saucy zucchini
directions: Brown beef and drain; set aside.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Layer the zucchini, onion, beef and macaroni in buttered casserole dish.
Combine celery salt, Tabasco sauce, salt, pepper and tomato paste.

Pour over layered ingredients. Microwave on Medium power for 12 to 16 minutes, stirring several times, or bake in a conventional oven for 45 minutes at 350°. Cover with grated cheese of your choice before serving.

title: barbecue dry rub
directions: Combine all ingredients in a clean coffee grinder. Rub on chicken directly or coat in a plastic storage bag. Make sure chicken is dry before applying.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: In a square Pyrex dish put a slight amount of olive oil in the bottom of the dish and
then
put
in the 4 packages of artichokes.
Let thaw out
for
a while.
Layer the artichokes with the bread crumbs and cheese and then add the salt, pepper and the chopped garlic.
On the
tops
of
the
layers add the bread crumbs, cheese, oregano
and
olive
oil.
Bake about 45 minutes in 350° oven until the
dish appears to be done.
Very delicious.

title: dirt cups
directions: *Or use Jell-O cook and serve pudding and pie filling prepared with milk as directed on package.
Refrigerate 2 hours before assembling dessert.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain peaches thoroughly on paper towel. Cut butter into cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly into greased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch), building up edges slightly.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: cookie press cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in cookie press.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: creamy pecan pralines
directions: Cook sugar, cream and butter until hard boil stage.
Test by dropping in cold water.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add pecans.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie tin.
Makes about 8 or 10 small pralines.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, green pepper, onion, celery, carrots, salt and 3/4 cup sugar.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour. Bring to a boil the vinegar, oil and 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Boil 3 or 4 minutes and pour over the cabbage mixture.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mrs. horowitz's summer cooler
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags; make a very strong tea. Squeeze and remove tea bags after 2 minutes.
Add the washed mint leaves.
Cool.
In a very large container, combine the lemonade and orange juice, adding water 3:1.
Add cooled tea and mint. Refrigerate.

title: russian salad
directions: Put water, jello, marshmallows and softened cream cheese over low heat and let dissolve. Remove from heat and cool till "milk warm". Add remaining ingredients congeal and joy!

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring to a boil the first 3 ingredients; boil 1 minute.
Lay the Ritz crackers in liquid, but do not stir.
Boil 2 minutes. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Cover with top crust; bake at 400° until brown.

title: cinnamon cream cheese danish
directions: Unroll 1 tube of rolls and place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. (Do not press together.)
Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Spread on top of rolls.
Unroll second tube of rolls and put on top of cream cheese mixture.
Pour melted butter on top. Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Combine sugar and 2 quarts water in large saucepan.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Cool. Add Kool-Aid and pineapple juice; mix well.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Pour over ice ring in punch bowl.
Serves 75.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Let frozen bread dough unthaw and slightly rise.

title: linguine a la margarita d.
directions: Put the vegetable oil in saucepan or melt the butter.
Add the squeezed garlic, lime juice, lemon juice, vermouth, salt and pepper; cook with medium heat for 20 minutes.
Add fresh, cleaned shrimp and cook for 6 minutes; don't overcook.
Make sure that the linguine is prepared so that it is finished to your liking at about the same time that the shrimp sauce is finished.
Serve with Chilean wine and
a nice smile.

title: eggnog for 1(very good and easy)
directions: Combine egg with sugar and salt.
Add milk and vanilla.
Serve cold in tall glass.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: raspberry swirl
directions: Line the bottom of a glass pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: low-carb pumpkin cheese cake
directions: In electric mixer, beat cream cheese and Equal until fluffy. Beat in eggs, pumpkin, cornstarch and mix in sour cream, spices and vanilla until well blended (beat 5 minutes). Pour into 9-inch spring-form or flat glass pan. Place cheesecake in a roasting pan with 1-inch of hot water. Bake at 300° until set in center (about 60 minutes). Turn off oven and let cheesecake cool 3 hours in oven with door slightly ajar.
Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: mediterranean winter soup
directions: Remove meat from bones of ox tails, lamb shanks and ham hock after boiling for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove meat.
To broth, add potatoes, carrots, onion and chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Add other meat.
Add cabbage, tomato paste, blood sausage and 1/2 cup rice. Simmer for 25 minutes.
Remove sausage and cut into bite size pieces.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar; blend.
Add unbeaten eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, which have been measured into flour sifter and then sifted.
Add nuts, etc.
Chill dough.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Do not flatten.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: marinara sauce (tomatoes)
directions: In large enamel kettle, saute onions and green pepper in oil until onions are tender.
Add garlic and saute 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer uncovered over low heat 3 hours or until thick, stirring every 20 minutes.
(I stir more often because in enamel pans food will stick very easily and you don't want to burn this.)
Pour into sterilized 1-pint canning jars, leaving 1-inch headspace; seal.
Following manufacturer's directions, process in pressure canner at 15 pounds pressure 25 minutes.
(If using a pressure saucepan, add 20 minutes to processing time.)
If desired, unprocessed sauce may be stored in refrigerator up to 1 week or frozen in airtight containers up to 3 months.

title: meatball stew
directions: Combine chuck, salt, pepper and breadcrumbs and shape into small balls.
Brown in small amount of oil.
Remove and set aside. Mix onion soup mix with 4 cups of water.
Drain oil from pan and add a little of the onion soup to the bottom and boil to remove the drippings.
Place the loosened drippings, the remainder of the soup and the remainder of the ingredients into large pot.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Season to taste.
Place meatballs into stew and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, flour and butter.
Add beaten eggs and pecans. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer.

title: pepperoni and chive mini muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients, except pepperoni. Stir until moistened.
Fold in pepperoni.
Spoon into 24 muffin pans.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes, until brown.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: hearty tortellini soup(makes 6 servings)
directions: In large saucepan, over medium-high heat, cook garlic in margarine for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add broth and tortellini.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add spinach and tomatoes.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Serve topped with cheese.

title: sweet potato cake *
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add water, then dry ingredients.
Stir in sweet potato, nuts and vanilla.
Beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in three 8 or 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: three flavor pound cake
directions: Cream
margarine,
Crisco
and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one
at
a	time,
beating	after each.
Sift flour with baking powder
and
add
to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done when tested.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Blend together and pour into crusts.
Keep refrigerated. Makes 2 pies.

title: pig's noses
directions: Mix all together.
Shake or mix frequently.
Store in dry place.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in frypan.
Add meat, onions and celery. Stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add bean sprouts and seasonings.
Cover and cook 1 minute.
Remove from pan and place in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and fold in.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to pan and heat thoroughly.
Spoon mixture-like pancake size batter onto pan and fry gently over low heat until eggs are set.
Turn over and brown the other side.
Repeat until all the batter is used.
Serve with rice and a brown gravy.
Serves 4.

title: black-eyed pea special
directions: Fry bacon in a Dutch oven until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving drippings in pan.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute celery, onion and green pepper in pan drippings for 5 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients and bring mixture to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until peas are tender.
Remove bay leaf; stir in crumbled bacon before serving.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: egg and vinegar crust
directions: Blend flour and Crisco until crumbs are size of tiny peas. Add all other ingredients and mix.
Let mixture rest at least 20 minutes; very important!
Divide and roll into crusts.
Makes about 5 or 6.

title: nacho dip
directions: *These amounts are approximate. You may change them to suit your taste.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine
first
four ingredients.
Sprinkle on chicken. Place chicken in
an
x 12 x 2-inch glass baking dish, skin side up. Bake
at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour
into baking dish, arrange chicken over rice. Cover
and
bake
minutes
longer
or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Serves 6.

title: cauliflower-ham chowder
directions: In large covered saucepan, cook cauliflower in chicken broth until almost tender, about 10 minutes.
Do not drain; set aside.

title: mandarin salad
directions: In a small saucepan, cook sugar and almonds over medium heat, stirring constantly, until almonds are coated and sugar is dissolved.
Watch carefully as they will burn easily.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour and salt together onto waxed paper.
Beat butter or margarine, sugar and egg in large mixing bowl at high speed for 3 minutes or until fluffy; blend in vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture to make a stiff dough; wrap in waxed paper; chill 3 hours or until firm enough to roll.

title: lemon lush
directions: Pat flour, butter and nuts into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° until golden brown (20 minutes).
Cool 20 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Prepare the hamburger by the directions on the back of the taco seasoning packet.
In a casserole dish, layer the can of refried beans first, then the hamburger mixture, followed by the Mexican cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven, top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, and sour cream. Eat with chips.

title: cheese cakes
directions: Place vanilla wafer in each muffin liner and put in muffin tin. Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar at medium speed of mixer until well blended.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour over wafer 3/4 full. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in Bundt pan.
Center may be real moist, due to the cream cheese.
This is normal.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out crust and cut in 12 squares.
Put 1/2 apple with 1 teaspoon sugar in center of each apple; fold over.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil, but don't cook.
Pour over dumplings.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: linguini with scallops
directions: Rinse and drain scallops.
Pat dry.
In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Cook garlic for 1 minute.
Add mushrooms and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add scallops and sherry.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until scallops are opaque.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put scallop mixture over linguini.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: strawberry jello pie
directions: Mix all but berries and cook until transparent of syrup consistency.
Cool.
When cold, mix with berries.
Pour into pie shell. Chill. Top with whipped cream.

title: lobster bisque
directions: Boil lobster tail (in shell) for 5 minutes.
Remove from shell and chop into medium size pieces; set aside.
Saute onion in butter until soft in a large saucepan; stir in flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Stir in chicken broth; continue cooking and stirring until mixture thickens and boils 1 minute.
Stir in diced lobster and sherry.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Blend in cream, tomato paste, salt and pepper.
Heat slowly just until hot.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat milk, margarine, sugar and salt.
Do not boil.
Cool to lukewarm; sprinkle on yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
In a large mixing bowl, put flour.
Make a well in the center.
Add liquid and mix well.
Cover and let rise until double in size, about 1 1/2 hours.
Knead on floured surface for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together and set aside the flour, soda, salt and baking powder. Blend together the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, beating until light and fluffy. Add flour mixture; mix well. Add oats, vanilla and chocolate bits.
Drop from teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Dough is crumbly. Yields 9 dozen small cookies.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all together and pour into dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grits with cream and cheese(classic and unbelievably creamy)
directions: In a heavy saucepan, bring cream and milk to a simmer.
Add grits, stirring, and return to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and cook 7 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent burning.
If grits begin to separate and turn lumpy, add a bit of water to keep creamy.
Remove from heat and add butter, salt and pepper.
Stir in cheese.
This can be made ahead and reheated in a microwave or over low heat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and use juice and enough water to make 1 can liquid.
Boil and add small package of Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool and add pineapple, cherry pie mix and nuts. Refrigerate.
Easy, pretty and delicious.

title: texas pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Stir well by hand.
Pour into greased bread pan or a greased Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Can be served as a dessert or a coffee cake.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix.
Add pineapple, coconut and vanilla.
Mix and pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: apple fritters
directions: Combine milk, egg and margarine.
Add orange rind and juice, apples and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Stir in milk mixture with a spoon until blended.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into one-half inch hot oil.
Fry to golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with white confectioners sugar.
Makes about 24 fritters.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut together and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and continue to cook, stirring until it thickens.
Remove from heat and add coconut.
Pour over cake which has been prepared according to directions on box in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: reese type bars
directions: Combine first six ingredients with 2 tablespoons water in a large bowl, beating until well blended and mixture forms a ball. Pat into 7 x 11-inch pan, smoothing top.
Melt and blend remaining ingredients together in double boiler.
Spread, smoothing over peanut butter mixture.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: mother's broccoli and rice
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli according to package directions. Set aside.
Saute celery and onion in 3/4 stick of butter. Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350° covered.

title: roasted carrots
directions: Scrape carrots; cut large carrots into lengthwise slices. Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine oil and butter; drizzle over carrots.
Sprinkle in salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn carrots and bake an additional 30 minutes. Yields 12 servings.

title: eggplant pizzas
directions: Wash eggplant.
Cut off ends.
Leave skin and cut in 1/3-inch slices.
Dip in egg, then bread crumbs.
Place on baking sheet sprayed with cooking oil.
Broil until crumbs are brown, about 1 minute per side.
Saute pepper and mushrooms in vegetable oil.
Set aside.
Place spoonful of sauce and a pinch of oregano on each. Add peppers and mushrooms.
Top with cheese.
Broil until cheese melts, 1 minute.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening, salt and sugar until mealy.
Add vinegar to egg and beat together with water.
Mix and chill for 1 hour.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes enough crust for 4 to 5 pies. For smaller amount cut recipe in half.
This crust is great for frozen pies.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar and beat until creamy, about 15 minutes.
Add condensed milk, half and half and cream.
Fold in the crushed cookies.
Pour mixture into a freezer and finish filling container with milk.
Prepare according to manufacturer's directions.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: carrot casserole(microwave)
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, microcook carrots and water, covered on High for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring once; drain.
Stir together mayonnaise, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Add to carrots in casserole and stir.
In a bowl, toss together crushed crackers, butter and parsley.
Sprinkle cracker mixture over carrots.
Cook uncovered 3 minutes.
Add cheese and cook 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese melts and mixture is heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese-stuffed chicken rolls
directions: Flatten chicken breasts between two sheets of wax paper so that they are of uniform thickness.
Place 1 tablespoon cheese near the tapered end of each breast.
Roll up the chicken tucking in the sides and secure with toothpicks.

title: aunt kay's version of swiss steak
directions: Pat ground chuck into patties. Fry or grill and drain off all grease. While meat is cooking, dice onion and cook in skillet along with the mushrooms. After meat has been cooked and drained, place in baking dish or pan. Add pepper and Worcestershire sauce to suit your taste. Drain any liquid off onions and mushrooms and pour on top of meat. Drain liquid off of peas and add to mixture. Add 1 can of water to soup, then pour on top of meat and vegetables. Bake at 350° from 1 1/2 to 2 hours (I like to bake it that long to thicken the sauce).

title: breakfast andies
directions: Use soft stale bread, not brittle. Or use fresh bread left to stand out overnight. Slice bread into cubes, 6 per slice (like drawing tic, tac, toe). Mix batter until smooth. Soak cubes in batter. Fry in hot oil, 1/2-inch deep. Serve on warm dishes with hot syrup, honey, jam (recommend never use toppings cold).

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and chill for 1 hour.
Stir and taste.
Add more dill weed, if needed.
Keep chilled.
Serve with mushrooms, celery, carrots, green onions, apples, cherry tomatoes, crackers and chips.

title: thumbprint coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with first portion of flour; let stand in warm place 30 minutes.
Then add second portion of flour.
Set in warm place 30 to 45 minutes.
Knead batter.
Put in three 9-inch well-greased pans.
Let rise again 30 to 45 minutes or until double in size.
Punch holes in dough with finger.
Add following topping.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook and stir onions, celery, green peppers and garlic in butter until onion is tender.
Remove from heat; stir in tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Add water, if needed.
Stir in shrimp.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice. Serves 6.

title: zucchini casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Place zucchini and onion in well-buttered 2-quart casserole. In a large bowl mix the sour cream, flour and egg yolks.
Fold in the egg whites.
Pour this mixture over the seasoned vegetables and top with the grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
A hearty yet light presentation of this versatile member of the squash family.
Zucchini, a form of summer squash, has only 5 calories per ounce!
It provides vitamin A, C and part of the B complex, along with iron, calcium, niacin, riboflavin and thiamine.
Adding cheese or milk to zucchini recipes raises the protein and calcium levels.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cover bottom of baking dish with any fruit.
Slice butter over the fruit, then pour batter of sugar, flour and milk over butter. Bake at 350° until brown on top or about 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients except the nuts.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into a ball or log and roll in nuts.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil two minutes at least.
Test in ice water for chewiness.
Add vanilla. Cool.
Put on ice cream.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Mix well. Combine rhubarb and strawberries.
Mix together; pour into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken in sherry
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces and dip in flour.
Brown in corn oil.
Salt and pepper after browning.
Pour off oil.
Add mushrooms with liquid and butter.
Allow butter to melt.
Add sherry and cook 5 minutes.
Put into a casserole dish.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: microwave lasagne
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, crumble up the beef and microwave for 5 to 6 minutes on High until the meat is no longer pink.
Drain off all fat and add the spaghetti sauce, water and salt.
Mix and again microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes.
In 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, layer 1/3 of the sauce, 1/2 of the uncooked lasagna, 1 cup grated Ricotta cheese (or the small curd cottage cheese) and 1/3 of the shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat the layers ending with the sauce.
Sprinkle on the Parmesan cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove and let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: corn bread sticks
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add eggs and milk.
Heat cast-iron stick greased with bacon drippings until sizzling.
Add mixture and bake in a 450° oven until brown.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Crush wafers and mix with melted butter.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch spring-form pan, leaving a 1-inch space to top.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a small bowl, whisk mayonnaise, sugar, and vinegar. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. In a large bowl, combine broccoli, cauliflower, oranges, onions, bacon, and raisins. Add dressing and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: unbaked peanut butter cookies
directions: Warm peanut butter and butter on the stove to a soft consistency.
Add powdered sugar, mix well, then add the walnuts and cereal.
Make into balls, dip in thin icing and roll in coconut.

title: quick and easy split pea soup
directions: *Grate some carrot shreds prior to putting whole carrot into blender.
Reserve and use them to garnish soup prior to serving.

title: cherry nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and
sugar;
add egg yolks, one at a time. Beat well.
Mix flour, nuts and fruit, then add to the batter. Beat egg whites and
fold
in mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hours.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with dressing until coated.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Line greased casserole with half of dressing.
Pour mixed ingredients over this and sprinkle remainder of dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook Minute rice according to instructions on box.
Melt margarine in skillet; saute pepper and onion in margarine.
(Dice pepper and onion before).
Mix this and all other ingredients together and put in chosen baking dish.
Top with grated cheese. Bake in oven at 375° for about 30 minutes; until cheese is bubbling.

title: crispy radish salad
directions: Wash and clean radishes.
Crush them slightly with the sides of a cleaver.
Wash celery and cut into 1/2-inch pieces; discard leaves.
In a medium size bowl, mix together soy sauce, oil and sugar; add radishes and celery.
Toss.
Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature. Add remaining ingredients, except paprika, and mix thoroughly. Spread waxed paper heavily with paprika. Roll cheese into ball. It will be soft. Cover with paprika. Wrap in waxed paper. Place ball in refrigerator until firm. Serve with crackers.

title: beef stew
directions: In medium bowl, mix thoroughly beef, sausage, bread crumbs, oregano and egg.
Shape into 12 meatballs.
In 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot oil, brown meatballs on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Add gravy, tomatoes, potatoes, carrots, onion, bay leaf and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 25 minutes.
Stir in peas; cook 5 minutes more.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 6 servings.

title: goodie bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine and pat into a greased pan. mix 1 egg, cream cheese and sugar together and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix oil and onions in frying pan; cook until soft, but not brown. Set aside. Mix all other ingredients; simmer until warmed, then add cooked meat. Simmer at least 2 hours. For thicker sauce, cook longer. Cook low and stir often. Do not cover while cooking.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together just before served so it is fresh.
Do not mix ingredients together ahead of time because it will wilt and the Fritos get soggy.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use 1/3 cup of mix for 1 cup of hot chocolate.
Just add boiling water.
Makes a large amount.
A good savings for a large family.

title: banana pulmoshake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend for 10 to 15 seconds.
Serve immediately.
Yields:
Two 6 ounce servings.

title: meatball soup
directions: When done, add cream and heat again.

title: squash casserole
directions: Place cut
up
squash
and
onion in water to cover and boil for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots. Mix
well.
Add
squash and onions.
Mix well.
Melt margarine and
mix
in
croutons
or stuffing.
Put 1/2 of the croutons
in bottom of square casserole dish.
Pour in squash mixture.
Put remaining croutons on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Then cut in shortening.
Mix well before adding water.
Add water a little at a time. Roll mixture into small balls (about 1 1/2 to 2-inches).
Let dough rest for 5 minutes.
Roll into about 8-inch size tortillas.
Cook in medium hot skillet 20 seconds on first side.
Then turn and cook until done.
Makes about 17 tortillas.

title: microwave cookies
directions: Melt oleo in microwave for 1/2 minute.
Add 1/2 cup milk and microwave 2 minutes.
Stir in sugar, cocoa, vanilla and salt. Stir well and microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir and microwave 2 more minutes.
Stir again.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and nuts, if desired.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Mix together well and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin bundt cake
directions: Thoroughly grease a Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the pecans, brown sugar and cut butter.
Sprinkle in bottom of Bundt pan.

title: baked tuna and noodles
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water and drain.
Add celery, onion, pimiento, mushrooms and tuna.
Melt margarine; stir in flour and salt.
Add milk gradually.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add to tuna mixture and pour into greased roaster inset pan.
Close vent.
Bake in electric roaster 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serves 50.

title: beef tapa
directions: Slice beef thinly to desired size (preferably across the grain) in a bowl.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and spread this on the meat.
Allow beef to marinate for at least 24 hours in refrigerator.
Fry in hot fat and serve.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Melt 1/4 cup butter, add onion, celery and mushrooms.
Saute until tender.
Stir in flour. Gradually add milk, cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add noodles, ham, salt and pepper.
Place in large casserole dish, bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Freezes well to reheat later.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix hot water, sugar, salt and margarine.
Add yeast and mix well, then add cup warm water, egg and half of flour to make soft dough and pour out remaining flour.
Add to dough and knead until smooth.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: fruit salad
directions: Use the juice from all the fruits and mix with vanilla instant pudding.
Dissolve and pour over the fruits, coconut and pecans. Refrigerate.

title: russ' scampi
directions: Stir butter, oil, onions and lemon juice in frying pan over medium flame until butter melts.
Add shrimp/prawns and cook 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until pink. Add salt, lemon peel, parsley and Tabasco sauce. Serve.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Blend butter, sugar, vanilla, salt and juice; beat eggs, one at a time.
Dissolve soda in sour cream and add to egg mixture. Fold in flour, nuts, preserves and food coloring.
Pour batter into 2 large or 4 small greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bread pulls away from pans.
Yield:
2 large loaves or 4 small loaves.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; blend until smooth.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Gently fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill.

title: venison steaks
directions: Place steaks in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with bacon.
Place onion rings over bacon.
Sprinkle diced green pepper over onion. Add spice to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Slowly melt chocolate and peanut butter.
Gradually fold in marshmallows.
Spoon onto wax paper lined dish.
Spread out evenly.
Chil until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In hot oil, brown one onion.
Add tomato sauce and cook to a paste.
Add tomato paste, whole tomatoes and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add remaining onion, celery, and bell peppers; mix well.
Add onion tops, parsley and water.
Cook to a thick sauce, but don't overcook; greens should remain whole.
Add shrimp, salt and pepper to taste and cook for approximately 30 minutes.
Serve over rice. Yield:
12 servings.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces under cold water after trimming any fat off.
Dry between paper towels.
Lightly coat with cooking oil and place in container or plastic bag with bread crumbs, a piece at a time.
Shake to coat with bread crumbs.
Place coated chicken pieces on cookie sheet lined with foil.
Sprinkle with a little paprika.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until cooked. Serve with Stove Top chicken flavored stuffing or Kraft macaroni and cheese and vegetables.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs and buttermilk that the soda has been added to.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt
and spices; mix.
Add prunes, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: super simple meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients, mixing together well. Shape into loaf and place in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and pineapple.
Add other ingredients.
Cool and form into ball rolled in chopped walnuts.
Serve on crackers. (Do not need to form ball.
Just add walnuts to dip.)

title: parmesan tomatoes
directions: Remove stems from the tomatoes and halve crosswise.
Place cut side up in a small baking dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients; sprinkle over tomato tops.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: raspberry-cherry pie
directions: Drain cherries and thawed raspberries; reserve 1 1/4 cups juice.
In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; gradually stir in reserved juice.
Cook and stir until mixture starts to boil.
Cook, stirring for 2 minutes.
Stir in butter and extract. Gently fold in fruit.
Pour filling into pie crust and top with a lattice crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mom's rhubarb cheese pie
directions: Put rhubarb, 1/2 cup sugar and flour in crust and bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Beat together cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and eggs; pour on top of rhubarb and bake for 30 minutes at 350°, or until knife comes out clean from center of pie.
Mix together sour cream, 2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Spread on hot pie, then bake for about 10 minutes to set sour cream.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: sugar free pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together and pour into shell.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg and beat well. Blend in applesauce.
Sift together next 8 ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture gradually.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Turn into 8-inch square pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan.

title: jello mold
directions: Boil crushed pineapple and 1/2 cup sugar for 5 minutes.
Add Jell-O and cool.
Mix 1 1/2 cups water to cream cheese, then add other ingredients.
Whip up the heavy cream and fold into mixture. Refrigerate.

title: almond apricot coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add the eggs, sour cream and extract; mix well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix well. Spread half of the batter in a greased and floured 12 cup fluted tube pan. Sprinkle with half of the almonds. Spread half of the preserves to within 1/2 inch of the edges. Cover with remaining batter. Spoon remaining preserves over batter to within 1/2 inch of edges. Sprinkle with remaining almonds. Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool in pan for 15 minutes. Carefully invert onto a serving platter.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium heat.
Add chicken, onion and pepper.
Cook and stir until chicken is cooked through.
Add corn, salsa and broth; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and cover. Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes and fluff with fork. Sprinkle with cheese and let stand 2 minutes.

title: * zucchini bread *
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil, zucchini, vanilla and lemon extract until light.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in 2 greased and floured bread pans.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Chop the first 6 ingredients.
Cook celery first in grease until half done.
Add in order the next 4 ingredients.
Cook until almost done in grease.
Add water and simmer until done.
Add large loaf of bread, which was soaked in one quart of milk.
Gradually add juice from giblets and about 3 to 4 pints chicken stock.
Add 18 raw eggs, 3 teaspoons black pepper, 5 teaspoons salt and 2 sticks butter.
Add crumbled cornbread made from 2 cups cornmeal. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Saute chicken livers in butter slowly until done.
Mash or cut them while cooking to hasten cooking, but do not brown.
Place livers and butter mixture in processor, using cutting blade, and process until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except egg, and blend.
Mixture should be quite soft.
If it seems dry, add a little mayonnaise.
Cool slightly.
Pour into 2 small wax paper lined pans and refrigerate until cold.
