Unmold and garnish with grated egg.
Serve with crackers or Melba toast.

title: trash
directions: Combine peanut butter, chocolate chips (Nestle) and margarine in double boiler until chocolate is melted and well mixed.
In a large pot, empty the Rice Chex; add peanut butter mixture.
Put half the box of sugar in white trash bag.
Pour mixture on top of Chex and add other half box of sugar.
Tie bag and toss back and forth about 10 to 20 times.
Delicious snack!

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In large skillet or slow-cooking pot, with browning unit, brown chicken in hot oil.
Drain.
In slow-cooking pot, combine chicken with onion, tomato sauce, oregano, thyme, salt, pepper, garlic and wine.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours.
Stir in drained mushrooms.
Spoon over hot, cooked spaghetti.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Lightly spray a 9 x 13 inch baking dish with vegetable oil spray. In a small bowl, combine 1/8 cup mozzarella and 1 Tbsp. Parmesan cheese. Set aside. In a medium bowl, combine remaining mozzarella and Parmesan cheese with all of the cottage cheese. Mix well and set aside. Combine tomato sauce with remaining ingredients. Spread a thin layer of tomato sauce in the bottom of the baking dish. Add a third of the noodles in a single layer. Spread half of the cottage cheese mixture on top. Add a layer of zucchini. Repeat layering. Add a thin coating of sauce. Top with noodles, sauce, and reserved cheese mixture. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake 30 to 40 minutes. Cool for 10 to 15 minutes. Cut into 6 portions. To reduce sodium:
Use unsalted cottage cheese. New sodium total = 196 mg.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Lay chicken in shallow baking dish.
Salt, pepper and sprinkle lightly with oregano.
Pour cream soup over chicken (no added water).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour with foil covering pan.
Remove foil and cover with dressing mixture.
Melt butter and add stuffing; mix and cover chicken with mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes uncovered until brown.

title: perfect cross ribs roast
directions: Sprinkle with salt and pepper.	Insert meat thermometer into center of roast.
Let stand at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roast in oven one hour.
Turn off heat.
Do not open oven door for one hour.	Very important.
During resting period, beef continues to cook slowly and evenly distributes heat throughout beef.
Turn oven regulator to 300°.
Allow roast to reheat 30 to 40 minutes until beef has reached desired internal temperature. Beef will be pink and juicy all the way through when it registers 130°.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook for 15 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Take off heat and stir in 2 (3 ounce) packages orange pineapple jello.
Stir good and put in jars.

title: 7 layer nacho dip
directions: Spread bean dip in shallow 2-quart dish.
Arrange avocado over bean dip, sprinkle with lemon juice and garlic salt In a small bowl combine sour cream and taco mix; spread over avocado.
Top with a layer of tomatoes and black olives.
Spread with cheese dip and sprinkle with green onions.
Serve with Tostitos brand tortilla chips.
Yields 6 cups.

title: scotcharoos
directions: In a big saucepan, mix sugar, Karo syrup and peanut butter. Bring to a boil.
Add Rice Krispies.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Broil chicken until done; cool and break into pieces.
Put broccoli on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan. Layer chicken on top of broccoli.
Make a white sauce of butter, flour, milk salt and Cheddar cheese.
Pour white sauce over chicken and broccoli; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: steak cosmo
directions: Brown steak in veggie oil.
Add onions and cook 2 minutes more.
Add carrots, gravy, mushrooms and seasonings to taste. Simmer about 10 minutes; then add celery.
Cook another 10 to 20 minutes or until carrots are done.
Serve over rice.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Beat egg lightly in measuring cup.
Finish filling the cup with milk.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder into bowl.
Work in shortening and mix with egg and milk, adding a tiny bit more milk if too stiff.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: italiano meat pie
directions: Make up Robin Hood pizza crust mix according to package instructions and press into a 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; set aside.
Brown beef in large skillet; drain.
Add green pepper; cook 2 minutes.
Stir in water, tomato paste and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle half of Parmesan cheese over bottom of pizza crust.
Put in 1 cup of Mozzarella cheese with meat.
Layer meat mixture, then Parmesan cheese.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 400°, then sprinkle top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: country hash
directions: Peel and dice potatoes (1/2-inch pieces).
Cut in small amount of water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine with leftover cut up meat and salt in buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly over low heat until mixture thickens.
Pour over ingredients in baking dish. Put in 350° oven, covered, for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells.
Drain immediately.
Arrange on a flat surface. Mix cheeses, eggs and bread crumbs in a large bowl.
Stuff shells with cheese mix.
Place shells on a baking dish (spread sauce on bottom of dish).
Spread sauce on top of shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Prepare broccoli, onion, bacon, raisins and cheese.
Mix together mayo, sugar and vinegar and pour over broccoli mixture. Chill for several hours.

title: speedy peach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dot the bottom of a baking dish generously with butter or other fat.
Pour the batter in a dish. Add 2 cups juicy ripe peaches, sweetened with 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
The batter will come out on top to form a crust.
Serve hot or cold, with or without cream.
You may substitute other fruits for peaches.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix with fork the first 3 ingredients.
Press into bottom of greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese (room temperature) with 2 eggs for 5 minutes.
Gradually add confectioners sugar. Beat until smooth.
Spread over first mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Mix up everything but Cheez Whiz.
Bake in casserole dish at 375° until bubbly all the way through (with lid).
Put Cheez Whiz on top and cook a few minutes until cheese melts.
Spread cheese evenly over top.

title: deb's taco salad
directions: Mix all together and then pour 1 jar of Catalina dressing over salad.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening
and sugar.
Add eggs and dry ingredients. Roll, cut and bake at 350°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Blend.
Add food coloring, water and cocoa.
Blend well.
Add buttermilk, flour and salt gradually.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Last add soda and vinegar and stir gently.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Chop all ingredients and put them in big bowl; add dry package and 1/2 bottle dressing to these vegetables.
Mix well.
Add noodles (cooked and drained) and add other half of bottle dressing. Mix all together.

title: baked chicken
directions: Cover in shallow baking pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon cucumber slices
directions: Blend ingredients. Cut cucumbers 1/4-inch thick. Top with 1 teaspoon salmon mix. Garnish with pimento. Cover and chill.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except Mozzarella cheese.
Place mixture into a 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with the shredded Mozzarella cheese and bake again until Mozzarella cheese melts.
Serve with crackers or bread sticks.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Drain.
Cut cheese in 1 inch squares.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Cover with cracker crumbs and bake in 400° to 450° oven until casserole is hot and crumbs are golden brown.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar. Combine remaining ingredients. Combine and put in a 9 x 11-inch pan. Freeze.

title: sauce for roast
directions: Place all ingredients in 1 cup measuring cup.
Add enough water to make 1 cup.
Pour over roast and cook covered until meat is done.

title: cocktail smokies
directions: Combine all ingredients except sausages and pineapple in a large saucepan over medium heat. Bring to a boil and let simmer for 15 minutes. Add sausages and reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Add pineapple for garnish and heat prior to serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine ingredients and place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain.
In large pan, add ground beef, onions, beans, chili powder, hot sauce, garlic salt, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Cook on medium heat for 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.

title: lemon lush dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and ground pecans together.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix sugar, half of Cool Whip and cream cheese together.
Mix pudding and milk until thick and pour over cream mixture.
Put in refrigerator.
When set, cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with ground pecans.

title: guacamole
directions: In a bowl, mash all of the ingredients together with a fork or potato masher until well blended but still chunky. Cover tightly by laying a sheet of plastic wrap directly on the surface of the guacamole and gently squeezing out any air bubbles. Seal the wrap to the edges of the bowl and refrigerate until ready to use, up to 8 hours. Makes 1 cup.

title: stuffed celery fingers
directions: Blend cream cheese with milk, pecans, dates and ginger. Fill celery with cheese mixture, cut each stalk
into
two
or three pieces.
Chill; serve on tray as
salad
or
appetizer. Yields 1/2 cup.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Cook at low heat to full boil.
Cool 5 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell and cool.

title: seasoned toast strips
directions: Remove crusts from bread; coat one side with cooking spray. Lightly sprinkle coated side of each slice with salad seasoning and cut into 4 strips.
Place strips on baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 16 servings. Contains 73 calories and 1.3 g fat per serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese until really soft.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise (salad dressing) together.
Add in milk, French dressing and Worcestershire sauce.
Rinse shrimp.
With a fork, break shrimp up until it is all shredded.
Add shrimp to mixture.
Chill.
Serve with potato chips, pretzels, crackers or Fritos.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli in 1 cup of water and bouillon cubes until done. Pour milk, flour and cheese, cut into cubes, into blender and process on grind.
Add to broccoli and water.
Stir in half and half and cook over medium-low heat until mixture thickens.
Stir frequently; will scorch easily.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and stem strawberries; save 5 or 6 for garnish.
Place strawberries in bottom of crust.
Mix sugar, Jell-O and cornstarch well.
Add to boiling water.
Cook until bubbles or begins to thicken.
Pour over berries.
Cool for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Top with Cool Whip and remaining berries.

title: tennessee cornbread  salad
directions: Prepare cornbread according to package directions.
Crumble half of cornbread into bottom of large serving bowl.
In another bowl, combine tomatoes, green pepper, onion, pickles and bacon; blending well.
Spoon half of vegetable mixture over cornbread. Stir together mayonnaise and pickle juice in small bowl.
Spread half of dressing over vegetables.
Repeat layering process with remaining cornbread, vegetables and dressing.
Garnish as desired. Cover tightly and chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lamb chop cucumber soup(approved ulcer recipe)
directions: Combine dry ingredients and put in airtight container.
Label and store in cool, dry place.
Yield:
16 cups dry mix (1 gallon).

title: garden fresh pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta salad as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients along with spice packet.
Refrigerate or serve immediately.

title: betty ann's cabbage rolls
directions: Mix hamburger, egg and rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add 2 or 3 tablespoons tomato sauce.
Put a spoonful in each cabbage leaf.
Roll leaf around meat tightly and secure with wooden toothpicks.
Put cabbage rolls on rack in pressure cooker.
Pour rest of tomato sauce over rolls.
Mix brown sugar, vinegar and water; pour over rolls.
Cook 10 minutes in pressure cooker or 1 1/2 hours without pressure.
After done, add sauerkraut, if desired.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: kids favorite peanut butter candy
directions: Mix ingredients together and press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Trim cauliflower.
Cook in boiling water until tender.
Drain. Divide into florets; reserve about 1/4 of them.
Force remaining through a strainer or puree in blender.
Melt butter and cook onion and celery for 2 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Do not brown.
Gradually stir in bouillon.
Add cauliflower, hot milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce coats spoon.
Beat egg yolk with heavy cream.
Remove soup from heat and gradually stir in egg yolk mixture.
Stir in sherry.
Add cauliflower florets.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: steak casserole
directions: Cut steak in bite size pieces.
Put in baking dish.
Add other ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and flour in bowl until smooth.
Stir in spinach, cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese and salt. Mix well.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake in oven for 1 hour.

title: oven-fried chicken cutlets
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In
small
bowl combine milk and seasonings.
Dip chicken
into
milk
mixture,
coating
both sides.
On a sheet of
wax	paper
dip
chicken into cornflake crumbs, turning to coat both sides with crumbs.
Place chicken on an aluminum foil-lined
sheet sprayed with vegetable spray. Drizzle 1/2 teaspoon oil over
each
cutlet
and
bake 8 to 10 minutes, turn chicken over,
drizzle with 1/2 teaspoon oil and continue cooking until chicken
is	tender and crisp, about 10 minutes longer.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Use glass bowl (large) and stainless steel knife to stir.
Use potholders because bowl will get very hot.
No plastic.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add egg and flavoring, then add flour and oats, a little bit at a time, until all mixed in.
Roll out dough and cut with cookie cutters.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for Ritz crackers and melted margarine.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish or Pyrex baking dish.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers and then melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until well heated.

title: texas style potatoes and eggs
directions: Melt butter.
Put in potatoes.
Fry until done.
Mix eggs in separate pan.
Mix until fluffy.
Pour into pan with potatoes. Stir until eggs are cooked. Remove from heat.
Serve with chicken or eat as a meal by itself.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Make topping of 1 package Ritz crackers and combine with 1 stick melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and oleo until smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Spread on cake; nuts may be put in filling or on top.

title: hog maw
directions: Mix potatoes, sausage, onion and seasonings (celery, if used) together.
Take one end of pig's belly and sew shut.
Then stuff pig's belly with ingredients.
When stuffed, close end by sewing or baking nails.
Cook in pot of salted water for about 45 minutes.
Then put in roasting pan and bake in oven until golden brown, about 45 minutes in a 375° oven (with lid on roaster).

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter in a double boiler.
Add onion, crab and seasoning.
Serve warm with crackers or chips.

title: sauerkraut and sausage bake
directions: In a skillet brown sausage; drain off fat.
Stir together sauerkraut and onion; turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Spoon sausage over sauerkraut mixture.

title: almond toffee candy
directions: Place almonds on well-greased baking sheet to form a 10 x 7-inch rectangle.
Combine butter, sugar, salt and milk in small saucepan.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until mixture turns to a light brown color.
Pour mixture over almonds.
Let cool.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Spread chocolate evenly over toffee mixture.
Freeze until firm.
Break into pieces.

title: sloppy joe pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large nonstick skillet, brown ground beef over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until no longer pink, stirring occasionally.
Pour off drippings.
Stir corn, barbecue sauce, green onions and, if desired, 1 teaspoon salt into beef; heat.
Place bread shell on baking sheet.
Spoon beef mixture over; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until the cheese is melted.
Cut into 8 wedges.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; stir in nuts.
Pour in crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until filling of pie doesn't stick to knife when inserted close to center of pie.

title: miss margaret's lo-cal buttermilk dessert
directions: Combine buttermilk and pudding mix.
Add Cool Whip.
Stir in drained fruit.
If desired, put into a graham cracker crust or a cooked pie crust.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Mix ingredients well except for chicken. In plastic bag, place the chicken, then pour marinade over chicken. Toss well to coat. Marinate for at least 12 hours or up to 24 hours, turning to evenly marinate.

title: peach sunshine(preserves)
directions: Add sugar to peaches.
Stir until sugar dissolves and peaches are juicy.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add peach Jell-O and crushed pineapple.
Bring to a boil.
Seal in hot jars.

title: wedding punch (diabetic)
directions: Mix in 1 gallon container.
Serve over ice and add 1 (2 liter) bottle Sprite or any lemon lime soda.
May be frozen and served mushy.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together. Use with steak, chicken or pork. Marinate 24 hours.

title: betty schultz's angel food cake
directions: Buy or make angel food cake.
Tear or cut up cake and layer in pan.
Whip Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix in nuts and strawberries.
Pour mixture over cut up cake.
You may layer cake and mixture alternately if you wish depending on type of pan or bowl you put it in.
Top with sliced fresh strawberries.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add liquids and beat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Cook beans and mash.
Mix remaining ingredients into beans. Mix well and heat.
Serve warm with corn chips or crackers.

title: peanut butter chocolate delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round baking pans.
In large mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs, vegetable oil, vanilla extract and sour cream. Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer.
Stir in boiling water.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pans to wire racks. Cool completely before frosting.

title: barbecue hamburg
directions: Mix together and boil.
Cook slowly for 1/2 hour.
Makes enough filling for 3 dozen buns.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well; chill for 1 hour.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Saute onion and pepper.
Add taco seasoning to ground meat.
Add all ingredients to crock-pot and simmer.
Top with Fritos and cheese.

title: peanut dip
directions: Mix yogurt and softened cheese with mixer.
Add brown sugar and vanilla.
After well blended, mix in nuts with spoon.
Great for sliced apples, bananas, grapes, etc.

title: 2 cheese balls
directions: Mix all this together (except beef) with hand, then roll cheese ball in smoked beef.
Save enough smoked beef to roll the other cheese ball.

title: gelatin cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add frozen strawberries and stir until the berries thaw.
Tear the angel food cake in one-inch pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the gelatin mixture over the cake and stir lightly until the mixture is pink; chill. Frost with whipped topping before serving.

title: swiss pie(similar to a quiche)
directions: Put grated cheese in a pastry crust (if adding extras, first mix in with cheese); then sprinkle with flour.
Mix milk, light cream, eggs, salt and pepper together, then pour over the cheese in the pie crust.
Scatter with plenty of bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes (first 15 minutes in hot 450° oven, second 15 minutes at low 325°).
Test with knife.
If it comes out clean, then it's done.

title: 15 bean soup - cajun style
directions: Soak beans.
Drain and add more water and 1 tablespoon salt. Cook until almost tender (time varies, usually 1 to 2 hours). Brown Italian sausage and drain.
Add to beans along with other ingredients.
Use seasoning packet with caution; it makes the beans very hot.
Continue to boil on medium to low heat.
Serve with cornbread.

title: plain old good chili(low-fat)
directions: Heat oil over medium to high heat in Dutch oven.
Add onion, garlic and green pepper.
Saute, stirring frequently for 5 minutes.
Add ground turkey and saute for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in flour, chili powder, cumin and cocoa.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Simmer chili, stirring occasionally for 45 minutes until thick.

title: viola's rapid mix angel biscuits
directions: In a large bowl thoroughly mix together 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, baking soda and undissolved yeast. Combine buttermilk, water and shortening in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat (120° to 130°) until liquids are very warm.
Shortening does not need to melt.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat for 2 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead about 20 to 25 times to form a round ball.
On a well floured board, roll dough out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut dough into 2-inch circles.
Place biscuits on ungreased baking sheet.
Cover; let rise in warm place free from drafts, about 1 hour.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes, or until done.
Remove from baking sheets.
Cool on wire racks.
Best served warm.

title: orange breakfast ring
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, sugar and orange peel until blended. Set aside.

title: fudgy chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl. Stir sugar, butter, choco bake, eggs, water and vanilla in large bowl. Stir in flour mixture. Stir in nuts. Spread into prepared baking pan. Bake for 18 to 22 minutes. Cool completely. Makes 2 dozen brownies.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Grind shrimp in a meat grinder. Chop bell pepper and onion. Mix all ingredients together; chill for at least 3 hours. Serve on crackers.

title: black bean enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large skillet, cook onion in oil for 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes, oregano and 1/4 teaspoon of salt. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Put into pan bigger than 9 x 13-inches (deep pan).
Layer in above order.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion, bell pepper and celery together, drain fat.
While browning sausage, cook soup as directed.
Combine rice, sausage and soup in casserole dish.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in water to cover in saucepan until tender; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Cool.
Combine potatoes with remaining ingredients in large bowl; mix gently.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Good in crock-pot to keep warm.

title: venison steaks
directions: Sprinkle
garlic
salt	and
lemon
juice
over venison steaks.
Let
marinate for 3 hours.
When ready to broil, heat an iron skillet until almost smoking.	Add 1/2 stick of butter which will
immediately brown.
Quickly put in steaks;
brown on one side.
Turn
and
brown
on other.	(Serve on the rare side.) Place
steaks on warm plate.
Add to skillet drippings, Worcestershire
sauce,
catsup and water.
Bring to boil; then pour over steaks and serve.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: To make crust:
Crumb together margarine, flour and dry roasted peanuts. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: moist pumpkin bread
directions: Beat shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, beating well. Add pumpkin and rest of the ingredients.
Spoon into loaf pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar and water.
Stir to dissolve sugar. Bring to a boil.
Add cranberries and return to boil.
Reduce heat. Boil gently 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Cool completely at room temperature and refrigerate.

title: curry appetizer
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add curry powder.
Blend well.
Add remaining ingredients, except chutney. Mix well.
Line a jello mold with plastic wrap and pour in mix. Refrigerate until set.
After it is unmolded, spread chutney on top.
Serve with water crackers.

title: bacon crisps
directions: Wrap 1/2 piece bacon around cracker.
Place wrapped crackers in toast pan.
Bake in a slow oven (200°) until bacon is done, about 45 minutes.
Let set a few minutes so bacon can crisp. Serve warm.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding mix as directed on pkg. but use 1-1/2 c. of reserved pineapple juice instead of milk.
When cool, fold in fruit and put in a glass bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: stern's special
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, brown sugar and Bisquick. Pat Bisquick mixture in pan and sprinkle with chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350°
for exactly 25 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Slice peaches and cover with sugar and cinnamon in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix well the biscuit mix, egg, milk, sugar, vegetable oil and cinnamon; spread over peaches and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Slice onions and green peppers into small pieces.
Place in olive oil in a frying pan.
Brown.
Add hamburger and sausage and brown.
Drain off all excess grease.
Pour all ingredients into a large pot.
Add some water as needed to get ingredients done. Cook on low heat to simmer all ingredients until done and seasoned, the longer you simmer, the better the sauce.
Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add brown sugar, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, oatmeal, chocolate chips, pecans, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Use 1/4 measured cup or ice cream scoop per cookie.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet 6 to a sheet.
Cook 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 5 minutes before removing from sheet. Makes 30 to 40 cookies.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill until time to serve.

title: can't fail divinity
directions: Cook sugar, water and salt until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cool water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and marshmallow cream.
Beat until it begins to thicken.
Add pecans and mix with a spoon.
Spoon out and let set.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Brown sesame seed in the oven at 350° until brown.
Cool.
Mix them into cream cheese and spread on celery.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Dissolve cranberry sauce in Jell-O mixture.
Mix in pineapple and pecans.
Chill until set.

title: yam bake
directions: Pour milk over oatmeal and let sit.
Mix all other ingredients together, mashing potatoes.
Blend with oatmeal mixture.
Pour into slightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and chopped pecans.
Bake until marshmallows melt.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, add egg yolks (save white for 7 Minute Icing if needed), or you can use 3 whole eggs.
Cream well. Add vanilla, cream, flour and red food color.
Let the milk be last, with the flour.
Cook in three well-greased pans in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for five minutes.
Remove cakes and ice with 7 Minute Icing or chocolate icing can be used.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased pan (round or square, deep dish).
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: green horseradish dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor or blender and blend until onion is pureed.
Use on greens or cold roast beef.
Makes 2 cups.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan to cake plate.
(I sprinkle powdered sugar on my cake plate before placing cake on it.)
Powdered sugar can be sprinkled over cake, but I prefer a buttercream icing.
Makes 16 servings.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil together all ingredients until tender (15 minutes).
Add milk and bring to a boil.
Thicken with cornstarch mixed with milk.
Turn heat to low.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Stir until melted.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Put beef in bottom of dish.
Place soup mix on top and mix with beef.
Put Tater Tots on top and bake at 400° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: chicken and bread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter casserole dish.
Butter several slices of bread and cut up into small squares.
Dice up cooked chicken.
Place a layer of bread squares, then a layer of chicken. Moisten each layer with chicken broth.
Repeat each layer until dish is full.
Dot with butter.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients in ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or use crock-pot.
Serve with toothpicks for a buffet.

title: baked crunchy trout
directions: Lay fillets in the bottom of a buttered 3-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with chopped onion.
Spread dressing over onion to cover fish.
Put crushed potato chips on top to cover completely.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4.
Easy and real good.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into a 9-inch crust and bake in 300° to 325° oven about 30 minutes or until firm.

title: broccoli dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in pie plate or shallow casserole.
Mix 2 tablespoons melted butter with 2 tablespoons mayonnaise and 4 slices diced bread.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sunday supper
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a heavy skillet, brown and crumble sausage.
Remove meat and drain well.
Line a greased 9 x 13-inch dish with the crescent roll dough.
Press edges together to seal. Sprinkle the sausage and cheese over the dough.
Combine the eggs, milk and pepper.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake 15 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: spicy meat loaf
directions: In mixing bowl, combine egg, milk, bread crumbs, onion, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Add beef; mix well.
Shape into a loaf in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cook, covered, at Medium-high for 20 to 22 minutes, giving dish a half turn once.
Drain off excess fat.
Microwaves vary so may your time.

title: italian rice pudding
directions: In a large pot, bring the milk, sugar and pinch of salt to a boil.
Add the rice.
Cook and simmer over low heat, uncovered, for about 40 minutes or until rice is soft.
Stir occasionally; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix the eggs, vanilla and half and half.
Beat until foamy.
Add all of this mixture to the rice mixture and bring to a slow boil, stirring.
Shut off the heat and place in a large casserole.
When cool, cover and refrigerate. Serve cold.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place 1/2 of stuffing mix on bottom of baking dish.
Put deboned chicken on top of this.
Combine liquid ingredients and pour over chicken.
Put remainder of stuffing mix on top.
Dot butter on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 425° oven.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Bring to a boil and let cook 20 minutes. Let set overnight and put in jar.

title: barbecue sauce(texas version)
directions: Saute 2 chopped onions in
butter;
do	not brown.
Add all other ingredients except liquid
smoke
and
sliced onion. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 pint.

title: pina colada cheesecake
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients except coconut and pineapple, mixing thoroughly with a hand beater.
Pour into a blender and add coconut.
Blend well.
Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Pour mixture from blender into pan.
Drain off pineapple and layer on top.
Place spring-form pan in a roasting pan half full with water.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour.
Let set for 3 to 4 hours before cutting.

title: favorite fruit salad
directions: Cut up fruit into bite size pieces.
Grapes can stay whole. Frozen raspberries do not have to be drained, the juice allows the salad to be juicy.
Mix and serve.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together 15 minutes on low heat.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low heat.
Stir often, adding more water if needed.
Brown and drain hamburger and/or sausage; add to sauce if desired.

title: best of show pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add extracts.
Sift flour, salt and soda together 3 times.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add grated rind and mix.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then reduce temperature. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: taco stew
directions: Brown meat and saute onions.
Drain excess grease.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Cook until done and well seasoned and flavored.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic, chili powder, oregano, basil and cumin.
Mix well.
Cook, stirring, for 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato paste, tomato sauce, sugar and salt; mix well.
Bring to boil; add beans and water. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes.

title: fritos chili pie casserole
directions: Place 2 cups Fritos in baking dish. Arrange chopped onions and half of the grated cheese over Fritos. Pour heated chili over onions and cheese and top with the remaining corn chips and grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: almond tea cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, milk and almond extract in large bowl until well blended.
Beat in sugar.
Combine flour, almonds and salt.
Mix into mixture.
Shape dough into balls with 1 level tablespoon. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Cookies will not brown.)
Remove and roll in confectioners sugar when cool.

title: chocolate raspberry yogurt pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in a large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved. Stir in frozen yogurt until melted. Stir in whipped topping and fruit. Refrigerate until mixture mounds.
If necessary, spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm. Garnish with shaved chocolate, additional whipped topping and berries, if desired. Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: fresh fruit cake
directions: Puree the oranges in a blender or food processor until the rind is finely chopped.
Reserve.
Mash the bananas; dice the apples into small pieces.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Gradually beat in sugar until mixture is thick and pale.
Beat in melted butter or margarine, then fold in oranges and bananas.
In a second bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and soda.
Beat into the fruit mixture, then stir in the apples, raisins and walnuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until it tests done with a toothpick. If desired, garnish with cherries.

title: backpack snack
directions: Measure dried apricots and place on a cutting board.
Chop into small pieces, using utility knife.
Place in a large container with cover.
Measure remaining ingredients into container.
Stir together with a large spoon.
Cover and store at room temperature.

title: instant brunswick stew
directions: Mix ingredients in a large pot or Dutch oven.
Heat well. Serve.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
From lemon, grate 1 tablespoon peel and squeeze 4 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice; set aside.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: mexican scrambled eggs
directions: In large skillet, saute onion, garlic, green pepper until tender in oil.
Add tomatoes, water, salt and pepper to taste. Cook 3 minutes.
Add eggs and cook over slow heat, stirring occasionally, until thickened.

title: never fail doughnuts
directions: Mix ingredients in enough flour to make a medium stiff dough. Roll, cut and fry in deep, hot oil.
Makes about 3 dozen doughnuts.

title: fig preserve cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, cinnamon, allspice, salt and baking soda in separate bowl.
Place small amount of flour mixture in small bowl.
Dredge pecans in mixture; set aside.
Add remaining flour and buttermilk alternately to creamed mixture. Add fig preserves and floured pecans.
Bake for 1 hour in tube pan, greased and floured.
Reduce oven temperature to 300° and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Mix onion soup and sour cream.
Let stand 2 hours.
Add 2 cups chicken broth to mushroom soup.
Heat slowly and add the sour cream mixture and blend well.
Mix with chicken and cooked rice. Heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 or more 9 x 13-inch casseroles.

title: tomato soup dressing
directions: Blend all and refrigerate. Kids love this dressing.

title: pineapple dish
directions: Mix and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled chinese beets
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a pan and cook for 3 minutes over medium heat or until the mixture thickens.
After cooling, store in the refrigerator.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in small bowl and chill.
Serve on crackers or bread.

title: nut cracker spread
directions: Blend the first 6 ingredients, then stir in the sour cream. Spoon into baking dish.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: seafood burritos
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix half of salsa with chili powder, toss with seafood, tomato, bell pepper and green onion. Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes, set aside.
Wrap stack of tortillas in damp paper towels.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Divide seafood mixture among 8 tortillas and sprinkle with cheese.
Fold bottom of tortilla up to partially cover filling; fold in sides to meet and roll over top to close.
Place seam-side down in baking dish and microwave 2 to 4 minutes.
Serve hot with remaining salsa and sour cream.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, in small bowl, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Into 10-inch baking dish, layer half of the broccoli and half of soup mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat at high for 5 minutes the eggs.
Gradually add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir in flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, salt and nutmeg.
Spread onto a large cookie sheet. Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. (Turn into towel while hot.)
Sprinkle towel with powdered sugar and roll while hot.
Let cool.
Unroll and fill with filling.

title: shrimp louis dip
directions: Mix well. Cover. Chill.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream pumpkin, oil and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and add with eggs.
Pour into greased cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Ice with cream cheese frosting.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown Polish sausage and onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients in a large casserole and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: poached fish
directions: Note:
Salt water fish is best, such as orange roughy or halibut.

title: chocolate chiffon cake
directions: Mix together water and cocoa.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Beat flour, sugar, soda, salt, oil, vanilla, chocolate and egg yolks together until very well blended.
Fold in egg whites.
Use a greased and flour dusted angel food cake pan. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Turn heat to 350° and bake 15 minutes.
Turn cake pan upside down on a bottle and cool completely before removing from pan.

title: low calorie frosting
directions: Combine pudding, sweetener and milk.
Beat slowly for 1 minute.
Fold in Cool Whip. Will frost a 9 x 13 cake. Store in refrigerator.

title: layered banana pie(sugar and fat free)
directions: Mix graham crumbs and butter and press into 9x13 inch pan. Layer with bananas, pudding, pineapples and top off with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour and serve. Note:
Fix pudding as instructed on box.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix sauce in blender and pour over carrots; add onions.
Let stand overnight.
Serve cold.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cornflakes).
Spread in 2 1/2 to 3-quart, buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave muffin toppers
directions: Note: Also great with pepperoni, sausage, peppers, onions, etc.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, bake at 350° for 8 - 10 minutes.
May be frozen to bake later.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip.
Fill shells and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream topping of your choice.

title: red cabbage
directions: Melt butter and add onion and brown sugar.
Cook until a golden yellow.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on high heat until steaming, then reduce to low heat.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes.

title: party cake
directions: Mix Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese; ice each layer of cake.
Add sliced bananas to each layer and top.
Add pie filling on top, spilling over sides.
Chill and cut with an electric knife.

title: aunt faye's battle hell (hot sauce)
directions: Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes (not under).
Remove from heat and stir in oatmeal.
Stir until oats are softened.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; stir thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper; let cool.

title: not nearly so complicated chicken luau
directions: Place chicken with water to cover in saucepan. Season with salt.
Simmer for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Bone and cut into bite size pieces. Set aside. Squeeze excess water from spinach.
Combine spinach, chicken and coconut milk in saucepan. Heat until cooked, but do not boil. Serve hot!

title: best easy chocolate cake
directions: Combine and sift flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add eggs, coffee, buttermilk, oil and vanilla.
(Very light olive oil can be used.)
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
(Batter will be thin.)
Pour into greased pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes for oblong pan.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat pieces with flour mixture.
Brown meat in margarine; add onions.
Saut until golden brown.
Add water, soup and mushrooms.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Just before serving, remove from heat and add sour cream.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: ground beef mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with half the corn chips.
Stir beans and enchilada sauce into ground beef mixture. Pour half the mixture over corn chips.
Top with the part of cheese, mix soup and picante sauce in bowl.
Pour over cheese, layer remaining corn chips, ground beef mixture and cheese over soup mixture.
Bake at 300° until cheese is melted.

title: candy apples
directions: Wash apples, dry and remove stems. Insert wooden sticks firmly in stem ends.
Blend sugar, corn syrup and water in medium-size saucepan.
Cover; bring slowly to boiling.
Uncover; boil rapidly, without stirring, until 1 teaspoon of syrup separates into hard, brittle threads in cold water (300° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat.
Add flavoring and coloring to tint bright red.
Dip in apples; reheat over very low heat, if syrup thickens.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add salt and sugar and mix well.
Blend in milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat in Cool Whip. Pour into pie crust and chill for several hours or overnight. Put cherries or favorite fruit on top.
Makes 2 shallow or 1 deep dish pie.

title: best ever sunny-side eggs
directions: I use small amount of margarine in frying pan.
Break eggs and drop carefully.
Cook a few minutes on low flame.
Add a teaspoon of water.
Cover quickly to steam.
Tops will have a thin white coating over yolk.
Looks like poached eggs when finished.

title: company cornbread
directions: Combine sour cream, corn, eggs and oil; beat well.
Combine cornmeal and baking powder; stir into corn mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: dandelion gravy
directions: In a frying pan, heat butter or oil and add enough flour to make a thick paste.
Brown nicely.
Add some cold water, stirring briskly until smooth.
Add milk gradually and cook to thicken. Remove from heat and add salt to taste and some vinegar and honey. Pour over prepared dandelion greens to suit your taste.
Add a few hard-boiled eggs and onions.
Pour this over potatoes cooked in their jackets.

title: slushies
directions: Put lemonade, Coffee Rich, and vodka in a blender; fill with ice.
Blend well and sprinkle with nutmeg; serve.
Yields approximately 5 servings.
Great on a hot day!

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and oil.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla; add coconut and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: corn and string bean casserole
directions: Place beans in bottom of casserole dish.
Place corn over beans.
Spoon soup over vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese over soup. Sprinkle pecans and cracker crumbs next.
Drizzle margarine over entire casserole.
Bake about 15 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: cabbage and cheese oven dish
directions: Cut up cabbage.
Cook and drain.
Stir flour into oleo. Gradually add milk. Cook until thick.
Add and stir until melted the cheese.
Pour over cooked cabbage in greased bowl. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: "pink stuff" fruit salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese with dry Jell-O. Add Cool Whip and fruit. Stir. Add nuts and cheese. Stir. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: cucumber-onion salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onion.
Blend together rest of the ingredients. Mix all together and chill in refrigerator for several hours.
Before serving, sprinkle with dill.

title: cyndy's summer delight
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Gently fold in squash and onions.
Combine stuffing mix with melted butter.
Put 2/3 stuffing mixture in greased 2-quart casserole; spoon in squash mixture and top with rest of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mama's pecan pie
directions: Mix all together in saucepan.
Cook until margarine is melted. Pour in uncooked pie shells and cook at about 375° until brown. Makes 2 pies.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli and rice according to packaging instructions. Mix cooked broccoli and cooked rice; add chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Fold in mushroom soup.
Place mixture in baking dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in a deep casserole dish.
Cook in oven, uncovered, at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: ham spread
directions: Blend in food processor.
Chill for 2 hours.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Serve with bread or crackers.

title: chex party mix
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Add Chex mix and nuts.
Mix until all pieces are coated. Heat in a 250° oven for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes. Spread on paper towel to cool.
Makes 7 1/2 cups.

title: chili squash
directions: Cut the squash
in
half
and set up in a pan.
You may need to slice a little off the bottom to keep it from rolling. Bake at 300°
until
tender
(you may add a little water while cooking to keep squash moist).
Divide chili into each squash and sprinkle with
grated
cheese.
Put
back into oven until cheese is melted. Add chopped onions, if desired.

title: heavenly coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is baking, mix sour cream, coconut and sugar.
Let set until sugar is dissolved.
Just before time to take out of oven, heat cream of coconut in small boiler just to boiling.
Remove cake from oven and poke holes in cake with long-tiered fork.
Spoon cream of coconut slowly over hot cake evenly.
When cake is cool, top with the coconut mixture to which thawed Cool Whip has been added.
Store in refrigerator.
Cake is ready when cool.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and sweet potatoes.
Add egg, milk, vanilla, raisins and nuts.
Put into a 4 x 6-inch pan.
Place marshmallows on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes until marshmallows are brown.

title: cranberry wassail
directions: Tie cloves and cinnamon in a cheesecloth bag; set aside. Combine cranberry juice cocktail, next 6 ingredients and spice bag in Dutch oven; bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Uncover and simmer an additional 20 minutes.
Discard spice bag.
Add ginger ale and cook until hot.
Yield:
17 cups.

title: pizza breakfast
directions: Press rolls into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Layer sausage, hash browns and cheese.
Mix eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars; add egg and vanilla. Mix well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place in ungreased small muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Immediately after removing from oven, press peanut butter cup into center.
Cool 10 minutes and carefully remove from tin.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Use broth as desired to make mixture workable.
Place in large baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° until desired brown.

title: christmas fantasy fudge
directions: You will also need 1 candy thermometer.

title: pam's spanish skillet
directions: Brown hamburger meat in a skillet.
Drain fat.
Add water and rice.
Cook until rice is done.
Add corn and allow all of the juice to cook out.
Sprinkle with cheese and let melt.
Enjoy!

title: pear crisp
directions: Sprinkle pears with Fruit-Fresh.
Spray a large 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Line bottom of dish with pears.
Mix other ingredients with pastry blender.
Sprinkle on top of pears.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until pears are done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans according to directions.
Drain water off beans.
Place beans in a mixing bowl; add soup, onion and almonds. Stir.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with onion rings. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 2-2-2 salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Thin mayonnaise with dressing. Pour over meat, grapes, celery mixture just to coat.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie crust for 10 minutes.
Fill crust with cubed tomatoes.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and basil.
Add garlic powder to taste.
Mix cheese and mayonnaise; spread over tomatoes. Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Delicious.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: Combine cheeses, spread half on bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Drain chilies and spread over cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Gradually add milk to flour; blend well.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour over cheese/chili mixture.
Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, cut into squares and serve. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: father's day treat
directions: Spread peanut butter on one side of 4 graham crackers. Drizzle a little honey over peanut butter; arrange banana slices over honey.
Top with other graham crackers.

title: coconut-oatmeal cookies
directions: In oven, toast oats and coconut until golden brown. Thoroughly cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla, beating well.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Stir in oats and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with a tumbler dipped in sugar.
If desired, sprinkle tops with untoasted coconut.
Bake in a hot oven (400°) for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove at once from pan; cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: In top of double boiler, over boiling water, melt morsels with sweetened condensed milk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly into wax paper-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours or until set.
Turn fudge onto cutting board, peel off paper and cut into squares.
Cover and store at room temperature.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients and press into a 9 x 10-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and let cool.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased container.
Cover with mashed Fritos.
Heat until bubbly and then serve.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar and Karo for 4 minutes in microwave.
Add peanuts and cook 3 minutes in microwave.
Stir vanilla and butter together.
Microwave 2 minutes.
Stir in 1 teaspoon soda and pour onto lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Do this quickly as it hardens fast.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: syrian pepper(da'a)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Especially good on lamb dishes.

title: special pork chops
directions: Brown chops in fat in frying pan.
Pour off fat.
On top of each chop, place on
onion
slice,
tomato
slice and pepper slice.
Evenly distribute rice over meat and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with water.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat 45 minutes.

title: white pizza dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In shallow 2-quart casserole, combine savory herb with garlic soup mix, sour cream, Ricotta cheese, 1 1/2 cups shredded Mozzarella cheese, mushrooms and pepperoni.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup shredded Mozzarella.
Bake 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with garlic toast.

title: corn casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and peppers in butter until tender.
Stir in flour.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients, except for 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with remaining cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: watergate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients; beat for 4 minutes. Grease and flour cake pans.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until done. Makes 2 (9-inch) round or 1 (13 x 9-inch) rectangular pan.

title: tuna pie
directions: Blend together eggs, sour cream, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Add tuna and cheese.
Mix together.
Place half can of onion rings on pie shell.
Add tuna mix.
Top with remaining onion rings.
Bake immediately at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden.

title: hershey bar oreo pie
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and combine with butter.
Press into 9-inch pie plate.
In a medium saucepan, melt marshmallows in milk over medium heat.
Stir in broken candy bars.
Cook, stirring, until candy is melted and combined.
Cool 15 minutes.
Whip cream and fold into chocolate marshmallow mixture.
Pour into crust.
Chill. Serves 6.

title: strawberry frost
directions: Puree berries in blender; add juices.
Add ice cubes one at a time; crush.
Pour into tall glasses.
Garnish with whole berries.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice.
Add onions and pepper when you add water to rice. Cook.
Drain artichokes, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Chop artichokes. Mix liquid, artichokes, mayonnaise and rice mixture.
Add olives. Chill.
Serves 4-6.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In a saucepan saute the first four ingredients in a small amount of oil.
Add the next seven ingredients and cook for at least half an hour or as long as you like.
When serving, shred Monterey Jack cheese and tortilla chips, broken into small pieces, into each bowl.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook vegetables
according
to	directions. Drain well. Place in buttered casserole.
Combine soup and cheese and pour over vegetables.
Bake,	uncovered,
for
minutes at 350°. Add onion rings for last 5 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: grandma's chocolate icing
directions: Bring to a boil on medium heat; boil, stirring all the time to prevent sticking and scorching.
Cook until it thickens and pour over cake.

title: holiday seafood spread or dip
directions: Rub mixing bowl with garlic.
Combine cream cheese and dressing and mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Let chill in refrigerator overnight or at least several hours. Serve with crackers or vegetable dippers.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: banana punch
directions: Heat water and sugar until sugar is dissolved and cool.
Add bananas
and juices.
Freeze everything except the ginger ale in milk cartons or whatever it will fit into.
Thaw about 2 hours and add ginger ale.
Will be "slushy." Serves 50 (4 ounce servings).

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread mix.
Stir well and add bread mix.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cornflake chicken
directions: Put cornflakes into a plastic bag.
Close the bag tightly. Use a rolling pin to crush the cornflakes.
Pour into a pie pan. Put butter into skillet; melt on low heat.
Remove from heat. Stir in salt and pepper until well mixed.
Rinse drumsticks under cold water and pat dry.
Place chicken on waxed paper.
Brush chicken with melted butter.
Roll each piece in cornflakes until coated.
Put chicken in a baking dish.
Be sure pieces don't touch each other.
Pour leftover butter over the chicken.
Bake in 375° oven 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: chicken-tomato souffle
directions: Melt oleo in heavy pan.
Add flour and stir.
Add chicken stock and cook gently.
Add tomatoes; beat egg yolks until thick and stir in.
Add diced chicken; then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in casserole about 40 minutes at 350°, or until knife comes out reasonably clean.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Place melted margarine, sugar, vanilla and cocoa into bowl. Mix until combined.
Add eggs and mix.
Blend in flour and baking powder.
Pour batter into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; do not overbake.
Yields 9-inch square pan.

title: honey barbecue chicken wings
directions: Partly cook wings in a 350° oven.
When almost cooked, remove from oven.
Mix honey and barbecue sauce together; brush on wings. Return to oven to finish cooking and finish basting occasionally with remaining sauce.

title: great depression cake
directions: In saucepan, simmer 1st five ingredients.
Cool.
Blend in flour, baking soda, baking powder, spices and nuts.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mamaw cora's egg pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and flour mix.
Add milk, oleo and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top of pie.
Set pie on baking or cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: punch(serves 100)
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: Melt margarine; add mustard, Worcestershire sauce, poppy seed and onion flakes.
Stir well.

title: marinated new potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 10 to 15 minutes or until tender. Drain and let cool. Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices. Arrange in a shallow serving dish. Set aside.
Prepare salad dressing mix according to package directions. Stir in green onions, parsley and pimiento.
Pour over potatoes. Cover and chill. Spoon potatoes over lettuce leaves, using a slotted spoon. Yields 8 servings.

title: gingered carrots
directions: In skillet, combine carrots and chicken stock.
Bring to boil. Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until carrots are glazed, about 2 minutes.
Can double recipe; freezes beautifully.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to package directions.
Add bacon-cheese to hot cooked grits; blend well.
Cool.
Combine beaten eggs with milk.
Stir into grits.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Garnish with crisp bacon curls if desired.

title: barbecue sauce(like darrell's)
directions: Mix all ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer for about 30 minutes to thicken.
Makes 1 quart.
Good on ribs, chicken, pork chops, baked or grilled fish and steamed oysters.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy donuts
directions: Make a hole in center of biscuits (a thimble works great). Put enough oil in frypan or electric skillet for donuts to be able to float. Heat oil to 400°. Add biscuits, turning quickly with fork when golden brown. Be sure and cook the donut holes too! Remove from oil and drain on paper towels.
Dip in a thin glaze of confectioners sugar and water, turning to coat both sides. Or sprinkle immediately with sugar, brown sugar or confectioners sugar. Simple but delicious!

title: onion dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Add sour cream and soup mix and blend well.
Refrigerate for several hours before use.

title: blondies
directions: Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Do not overcook. Blondies should be slightly chewy.
Bake in greased pan, approximately 11 x 15 x 1-inch, or can be divided into 2 smaller pans (not too deep).
Batter will rise during cooking, but will fall and crack while cooling.
Cut when cool.

title: peanut delights
directions: Melt chocolate bits in a double boiler on low heat.
Take away from heat.
Add milk and peanuts.
Drop teaspoons of mixture onto wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Beat butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Mix in flour and walnuts until crumbly; reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining mixture in pan. Bake for 12 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and granulated sugar.
Beat in remaining ingredients until smooth.
Spread cream cheese mixture over crust; sprinkle with reserved mixture.
Bake until center is firm, about 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 25.

title: carnation famous fudge
directions: Grease 8-inch square baking dish.
In medium saucepan, combine butter, milk, sugar and salt.
Bring to full, rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in marshmallows, chocolate morsels, nuts and vanilla.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute or until marshmallows melt.
Pour into pan.
Cool completely.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: nobby apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in diced apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans and mix.
Add pepper and onion.
Mix oil and vinegar with the rest and pour over bean mixture and toss. Refrigerate covered until served.
Keeps hours ahead.
Serves:

title: company salad
directions: In medium size bowl, place cottage cheese, dry Jell-O and Cool Whip.
Stir until combined.
Add drained fruit; chill several hours until thick.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: dream cake
directions: Bake cake per box directions.
Pour pineapples over the cake. Mix pudding and cream cheese together and pour over cake.
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: barbecued bacon shrimp
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: raspberry tang salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool.
Fold remaining ingredients in order given (including pineapple juice).
Pour into ring mold or 8-inch square pan.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Leave cream cheese at room temperature.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and milk.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for a day.
Put pie filling on top before serving.

title: fruit cake
directions: Melt margarine at room temperature.

Beat eggs, margarine, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice together. Mix nuts in 1/2 flour. Mix candied cherries and pineapple in the other 1/2 of flour. Then mix all ingredients together. Bake in tube pan at 250° for 2 hours.

title: vera's chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and milk a little at a time, starting and ending with flour, and beat well.
Add melted chocolate, then add vinegar, salt and soda which have been dissolved together.
Beat well, and bake in two 9-inch greased and floured pans, about 30 or 35 minutes at 350°.
Frost with favorite icing.

title: chili chuck
directions: Trim fat; cut meat into thin strips or cubes.
Sprinkle with flour.
In skillet, brown meat in oil; pour off fat and add tomatoes, water, onion and chili powder.
Cover; cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Stir now and then, add soup and green peppers.
Cook, covered, 1/2 hour more or until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: ting-a-lings
directions: Combine morsels in double boiler and melt until smooth. Use low heat.
Remove from heat.
Immediately stir in chow mein noodles (careful not to break up too much).
Quickly spoon out onto wax paper in tablespoon size.
Let sit until dry.
Enjoy!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and saute until clear.
Add broccoli.
Stir thoroughly.
Add soup and simmer for several minutes.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add cooked rice.
Put in buttered dish and bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Shape into patties.
Fry in hot grease.
Brown on both sides.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix shortening, flour and salt; then add liquids.
Makes 4 crusts.

title: tortilla triangle
directions: Mix chopped chilies and ripe olives and softened cream cheese. Spread over first tortilla and then top with another tortilla. Cut into wedges with pizza cutter.
Continue with mixture and tortillas until finished.
Serve with picante sauce to the side. Will keep in airtight container in refrigerator for a week.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Parboil broccoli and cauliflower.
Mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream and almonds.
Add to broccoli and cauliflower.
Pour into prepared casserole; cover with buttered crumbs.
Heat until bubbly.

title: pressed butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 4 ingredients.
Then work in the sifted flour.
Add additional flour, if needed, to make dough stiff enough to go through cookie press.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes, just until cookie dough is set but not browned.
Remove on cookie rack.
Store in closed container.

title: crock-pot turkey breast
directions: Salt turkey breast and place in crock-pot.
Mix soup with the water.
Slowly pour over top of turkey breast.
Cover and bake slowly, 8 to 10 hours or until done.
Let turkey breast rest on platter before serving.
The drippings make a nice base for gravy.

title: mike's bean salad
directions: Wash
and drain beans (remove pork).
Add tomato, onion and green pepper and mix with mayonnaise.
Refrigerate several hours. Time of preparation: 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Sprinkle small package of jello over the cottage cheese.
Add the thawed Cool Whip.
Fold in the fruit and chill.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans evenly in bottom of well-greased Bundt cake pan.
Combine the 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits in fourths; roll in sugar mixture.
Layer in pan.

title: hummingbird cake(one says m-m-m-m at the first bite)
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in eggs only until moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon into 3 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove and cool (especially good after 24 hours).

title: jean's potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion until tender.
Add soups and cornstarch to thicken.

title: grandma's egg bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Add well beaten egg. Stir baking soda into buttermilk; add to mixture.
Melt Crisco and add.
Pour into hot, well-greased 9-inch black iron skillet.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until brown and crusty.

title: raspberry cheese coffee cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese and margarine with an electric mixer on medium to high speed about 30 seconds or until combined.
Add about half of the flour to the cream cheese mixture; beat until combined.
Add the sugar, eggs, milk, baking powder, baking soda and vanilla to cream cheese mixture.
Beat on low speed until well mixed. Increase to medium speed for 2 minutes.
Beat in remaining flour on low speed just until combined.

title: barbecue ribs and sauce
directions: To make thinner, add 1 or 2 cups water.
Brush sauce on ribs when they are almost desired tenderness.
Allow to continue cooking for a short time, turning frequently to prevent burning.

title: hot casserole
directions: Cut sausage in thin slices and chop onion in.
Cook slow, do not brown.
Stir in other ingredients; cook on top of stove, about 25 minutes or until done.
Add water, if necessary.
Do not let it get dry.
If sausage is not hot, add pepper.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt. Mix ingredients all together; place in a buttered casserole dish (9 x 12-inches). Top with 1/2 to 3/4 cup grated cheese and 1 cup Chinese noodles. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into an unbaked pie shell (9-inch) and bake in 350° oven 45 to 50 minutes. Cool and top with cream, ice cream, Cool Whip or serve plain.

title: ice cream bars
directions: Mix corn flakes, coconut, nuts, sugar and butter.
Pour 2/3 of mixture into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Slice ice cream and place on cereal mixture.
Sprinkle remaining mixture on ice cream.
Cover and freeze until firm, at least 4 hours.
Cut into bars.

title: blueberry cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Rinse blueberries from mix with cold water and drain.
Cut butter into mix with pastry blender or 2 knives.
Stir in finely chopped pecans.
Press into bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until set.
Blend cream cheese and sugar until smooth in a large bowl.
Add egg, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Beat well.
Spread over baked crust.
Sprinkle with blueberries.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Add egg; mix well.
Spread onto bottom of pie shell.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Carefully pour over cream cheese mixture; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes. Cool.
Brush with maple syrup and garnish with whipped cream and nuts, if desired.
This pie melts in the mouth.

title: the big cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease round pizza pan.
In large bowl, put in butter and sugars and cream together with mixer until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla until well blended.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well with wooden spoon.
Spoon in chocolate chips and mix well.
Spread mixture of dough to edge of pan, being sure dough is evenly spread.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool and cut into 16 wedges.

title: crock pot roast
directions: Season with salt & pepper.
Brown roast on both sides. Combine soups and heat until smooth.
Put roast in soup in crock pot and cook until tender; usually 6-8 hours.

title: cheese-meat loaf
directions: Chop onion and mix all ingredients well. Shape into a loaf in a baking pan. Bake at 350° about 1 hour until browned. Makes 6 servings.

title: mom's molasses cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix egg, sugar and shortening.
Add molasses and warm water.
Slowly mixin dry ingredients.
Add raisins.
Drop by tablespoon on buttered cookie sheet and bake at 350° for approximately 7 minutes or until done. Your kitchen will smell great!

title: raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins an inch or so over the top with water.
Cook until good and plump over low heat.
Mix together sugar, salt, cinnamon and flour. Add enough water to make it like a thickening for gravy.
Stir into raisins and continue cooking over low heat until thick.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust and make a lattice top. Sprinkle with a little cinnamon and sugar and bake at 350° until golden.

title: vegetable sauce for dipping
directions: Blend together.
This dip is delicious for shrimp or raw vegetables such as cauliflower, cucumber and raw squash, sliced. Yields 1 1/2 cups.
This dip will keep for weeks.
Keep refrigerated.

title: old-fashioned butterscotch refrigerator cookies
directions: Beat together brown sugar, butter and eggs.
Add flavorings. Mix together dry ingredients and add to the mixture.
Add nuts. Shape into loaves, wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Slice cookies very thin and bake at 350° until light brown.
Do not overbake.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Boil 2 to 3 minutes the oleo and brown sugar.
Stir in nuts. Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Separate and store in tight container.

title: almond cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar until fluffy.
Add everything except the cherries.
Mix well with your hands.
Take a heaping teaspoonful of dough and start to form into a ball; push in half a cherry and roll again into a perfect ball.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in slow oven, 325°, for 35 minutes.
While hot, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together the eggs and sugar.
Sift flour twice.
Add 1/3 of flour and 2 eggs at a time.
Blend well after each addition. Stir in vanilla.
Bake in greased stem pan at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: In baking dish, place in layers raw potatoes, cheese, soup and seasonings.
Cover tightly with lid or foil and place in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mock crabmeat salad
directions: Combine parsnips, celery, pimento and olives.
In separate bowl, blend mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion and salt.
Add to parsnip mixture and toss lightly.

title: salad
directions: Drain all juices and boil.
Then add 2 tablespoons flour or cornstarch to thicken.
Pour into cooked macaroni.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, add Cool Whip, fruits and nuts.

title: heavenly divine
directions: Mix sugar, flour, vinegar and juice from drained pineapple in saucepan; cook until thick.
Add two beaten eggs; cook more.
Cool and add bananas, drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cookies to live for
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking soda in a medium size bowl. Cut butter with pastry blender or 2 knives, until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Add milk, lemon peel and vanilla; stir with a fork until moistened.
Gather dough; press into a ball, then shape into a 7 x 2 x 12-inch rectangle.
Wrap and refrigerate at least 1 hour, until firm.

title: fruit shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend until frothy. Serve immediately.
Makes 1 serving, 110 calories per serving.

title: quick snack
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients.
Pour over the Rice Chex (use large bowl).
Mix well until all ingredients are coated well.
Pour box of sugar over mixture and mix well again.
Store in airtight container.

title: sweet-tang stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in wok.
Add garlic, then broccoli and onion.
Stir and cook for a couple of minutes.
Add 1/3 cup wine and mushrooms; cook a minute.
Add honey and sesame seed.
Add torn up kale and remaining wine.
Add rosemary and a couple of dashes of tamari. Cover and simmer until kale is tender.
Stir and serve over Quinoa or rice.

title: oklahoma cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes in a greased and floured sheet cake pan.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: In bowl, mix flour, oats, sugar, baking powder and salt.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Pour in pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut over cake.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour over cake. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: In large wok, heat olive oil.
Add chicken, mushrooms, onions, ginger and garlic.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Add carrots and celery and cook until tender.
Add remaining vegetables and soy sauce.
Don't overcook these vegetables.
